title: irish italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Working a cattle drive down the canyon to market in Bakersfield when I was 14 years old, and bringing all the horses back, just me alone.

title: herb green peas
directions: In heavy saucepan, heat peas.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly.
Serve immediately.

title: crab dip
directions: Remove shells from crab meat.
Mix all ingredients except crab and 1/2 of Cheddar cheese.
Fold in crab meat and sprinkle remaining Cheddar on top.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, covered, then 15 minutes, uncovered.
Serve hot!

title: microwave fantastic fudge
directions: In two quart batter bowl, combine evaporated milk, butter, sugar and marshmallows.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High or until marshmallows puff and mixture begins to boil.
Stir.
Reduce setting.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes on 6 or until mixture boils and sugar dissolves completely.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts, and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Spread in buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cool.
Cut into one-inch squares.
Yields 64 pieces.

title: graham cracker surprises
directions: Boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Use perforated graham crackers, broken.)
Cover crackers on a greased jelly roll tin. Sprinkle with nuts and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Be sure to watch to prevent burning. This is a real favorite and so easy to make on short notice.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Dip chicken breasts in egg/water mixture. Roll chicken breast in Ritz cracker crumbs. Saut chicken in butter until brown on both sides. Place in baking dish. Add 3-4 tbsp. of butter; cover dish with foil. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Ten minutes before dish is done; sprinkle parsley and shredded or sliced Swiss cheese on top of chicken. Continue baking for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: plain totopos(plain corn chips)
directions: Cut tortillas into strips, squares or triangles with scissors or sharp knife.
Using tongs, deep fry in hot oil for 10 seconds. Drain on paper towel.
Excellent with cheese dip.
Makes about 50 to 60.

title: marvelous fruit medley
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill about 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.

title: lila's beet pickled eggs
directions: Mix together the pickled beets, vinegar, sugar and salt. Bring to a boil.
Pour over the hard-boiled eggs.
Refrigerate.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients, then pour into ice cream freezer.
Fill with milk to the line and start.

title: queso dip
directions: Saute first 2 ingredients.
Combine chilies, soup, milk and cubed cheese.
Mix onion and cheese mixture.
Slow cook or microwave until melted.

title: chicken karahi
directions: Fry onion.
Add chicken, salt, red pepper, cumin and garlic. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Cook it on medium flame.
When chicken is cooked, add green pepper.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add fresh coriander on top and serve it hot.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Combine with melted margarine. Spread over casserole.
Brown about 5 minutes.

title: saucy tomato burgers
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, sour cream, 1 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 patties.
Brown in a skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Add Hunt's sauce, Worcestershire sauce and remaining salt.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Put in baking dish.
Top with bacon and cover.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
(May be uncovered toward the end of baking time.)

title: kahlua fudge topping
directions: Stir cocoa and sugars together in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan. Add cream, Kahlua and butter.
Stir over medium heat until mixture begins to boil.
Keep at a boil, stirring 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cool and store in covered jar in refrigerator. Serve warm or at room temperature.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.
Just pour over ice cream, or layer it in a parfait.
Good too with cake or brownies, topped with ice cream.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Shred tortillas into small pieces.
Coat the bottom of a two to three-quart casserole with oil.
Cover the bottom with a thin layer of green chili.
Layer tortillas, chicken, onion, cheese and salsa.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: panzerotti
directions: Let dough rise.
Heat and season tomatoes to taste.
Roll dough into circles approximately 8 to 10-inches in diameter.
Top with tomato and cheese as though making small individual pizza.
Fold over and press edges together as you would a turnover.
Fry over wood fire until medium golden color.
Drain on paper towels. Experiment with additional fillings of your choice.
Try to cook these in wine box oven.
Use 6 to 8 pieces charcoal.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs. Sprinkle bread crumbs on bottom of buttered casserole dish. Add squash mixture. Cover with more bread crumbs and add generous dots of butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and boil 1 hour or until liquid is absorbed and the rice is tender. Remove from heat and add the egg yolks, evaporated milk and cinnamon to taste.

title: tea brownies
directions: Make any cake batter except angel food, sponge or chiffon. Spread in greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Cool in pan.
Make a white fluffy frosting.
Divide into small bowls; tint.
Cut cake into diamond, square and triangle shapes and frost in different colors. Trim with rosettes, chopped nuts, silver shot, gumdrops, candy sprinkles, chocolate pieces or maraschino cherries.

title: "some moore" spaghetti
directions: Saute onion in oil about 10 minutes over medium heat or until soft.
Add
remainder
of
ingredients
except
cheese. Simmer on low heat at least 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Put cheese in large bowl.
Add sauce and stir until cheese is melted.
Mix in cooked spaghetti or small pasta shells.

title: mincemeat holiday cake
directions: Combine mincemeat, nuts, rum flavoring and vanilla extract. Line bottom of 9-inch tube cake pan with heavy brown paper.
Blend mayonnaise and buttermilk in mixing bowl.
Stir flour, sugar, salt and soda over mayonnaise mixture.
Add orange rind, candied fruit and maraschino cherries and mix well.
Then stir in mincemeat mixture.

title: * chili rarebit *
directions: Fry bacon in skillet over medium flame until crisp.
Remove, drain and crumble.
Pour all but 2 tablespoons of drippings from skillet.
Add onion and saute about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese melts. Serve over toast or toasted English muffins.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry nut salad
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil in large pan.
Add cherries and juice.
Bring back to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add jello. Stir to dissolve.
Add pineapple and juice.
Stir in Pepsi and nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Cool Whip when set.

title: date nut rolls
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine, 1 cup chopped nuts, egg and vanilla flavoring over medium heat about 10 minutes or until thick.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Roll into ball and then roll in coconut.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs and add.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Blend in nuts, fruit and cherries.
Form in rolls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in plastic wrap and freeze overnight. Place on greased baking sheet and bake for 8 minutes at 375°.

title: wrapped chicken breasts
directions: Soak dried beef in water 15 minutes if it came in a jar. Arrange beef slices on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Wrap each chicken breast half in a slice of bacon; place over dried beef.
Combine sour cream, mushroom soup and sliced mushrooms; pour over wrapped chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours; uncover during last 1/2 hour of baking time.
Serve hot with rice or noodles.
Makes 10 servings (really makes 5 servings because everyone wants 2).

title: tex-mex two bean chili
directions: Drain beans and rinse.
Heat oil in 6-quart pan.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic for 3 to 4 minutes or until tender.
Add stew meat and sausage, stirring to crumble sausage.
Cook 5 to 6 more minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix together.
Add enough mayonnaise to thin mixture for dipping.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt together over low heat. Stir often. Pour in a cookie sheet. Cool. Can freeze these. Or pour in small muffin cups.

title: chocolate glaze frosting
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cocoa, syrup, water and shortening.
Stir over low heat until shortening melts and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat and beat in sugar and vanilla.

title: bacon-peanut spread
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Grind bacon, peanuts, eggs and pickles.
Mix with salad dressing (Kraft).
Serve on rye crackers or make sandwiches.

title: beef roll-ups milanese
directions: Pound meat until quite thin; cut in 3-inch squares.
Moisten each piece with soy sauce; rub with garlic.
Set aside.
Press out and discard excess liquid from thawed spinach.
In mixing bowl, combine bread crumbs, salami, salt, pepper, thyme, Accent and paprika.
Mix thoroughly with hand.
Blend in spinach.
Add a little broth while mixing to hold dressing together.
Spread thin layer of dressing on each piece of meat.
Roll up and tie both ends with string.

title: zucchini crisp
directions: Mix together the butter, flour and sugar until crumbly.
Save out 2 cups mixture and pat remaining into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: stir-fried tomatoes, pepper and onions
directions: Slice a large tomato into 8 wedges.
Slice a large onion into 1/8-inch thick layers.
Dice 1 to 2 green peppers into 1-inch squares.
Heat oil or wine in preheated wok.
Stir-fry onions for 1 minute, cooking for 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and allow to cook 1 minute longer, tossing ingredients as needed.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Melt butter in a long rectangular dish (Pyrex).
Add crushed pretzels and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Mix and spread evenly.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.
Set aside to cool thoroughly.
Whip softened cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and whipped topping, mixing well.
Spread over cooled pretzel crust.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add frozen strawberries, separating with fork.
Spoon this over cream cheese mixture.
Chill for several hours until firm.
Serve in squares.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into 3 greased 8 x 4 pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool on racks.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix Dream Whip, milk and flavoring until it gets stiff.
Then soften cream cheese and add cup of sugar.
Mix all these ingredients together.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and put cherry pie filling on top.
Put in freezer and let set up.
Keep frozen.

title: herbed carrots
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine butter, water and sugar.
Add quartered carrots.
Cover tightly.
Cook over low heat
for 15 to 20 minutes.
Season to taste.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley and dried, whole tarragon (crushed).
Don't drain.
Serves 6.

title: grilled chicken roll-ups
directions: Combine juice, mustard and brown sugar.
Set aside.
Cut chicken breasts in half lengthwise.
Roll each strip, wrap with 1 piece of bacon and secure with toothpick.
Grill 30 to 40 minutes, basting with sauce every 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Make rice according to package directions, add almonds and then cool.
Mix together onions, bell pepper, water chestnuts, olives, sour cream, mayonnaise, artichoke hearts, dill weed and basil.
Add to Rice-A-Roni.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Melt both chocolates over hot water.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to chocolate; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen.

title: broccoli cashew salad
directions: Chop broccoli and onions; add raisins and cheese.
Mix mayo, vinegar, sugar and mustard.
Pour over salad and toss.
Add cashews just prior to serving.

title: heavenly cake
directions: Bake cake as directed; cool.
When cake is cool, crumble.
Put half of crumbs into a long glass dish.
Top with layers of the following:
1/2 can pie filling, 1/2 instant pudding (prepared), 1/2 can crushed pineapple, 1/2 of banana slices and 1/2 whipped topping.
Repeat layers, beginning with crumbs.
Garnish with coconut, pecans or cherries.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes with mixer. Melt butter and add to potatoes. Add sugar and salt. Beat eggs, add vanilla, flour and spices. Pour mixture into greased pan. For topping, mix together remaining flour, butter, sugar, and pecans. Place on top of potatoes. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: granny rolls with my variations
directions: *For diabetics, yeast will feed on one cooked, mashed potato in lieu of sugar.

title: orange julius(drink)
directions: Place all ingredients into blender at same time.
Blend approximately 10 seconds (leave some texture) and serve cold.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in casserole. Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and bake for 25 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: apple nut dip
directions: Beat sour cream, cream cheese and cinnamon in a medium bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with fruit dippers, pound cake or angel food cake cubes.
Makes 3 1/4 cups.

title: scalloped potatoes with pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in hot oil in 12-inch skillet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Meanwhile, melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, chicken bouillon and water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Place potatoes in bottom of 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with onion rings.
Pour chicken broth mixture evenly over potatoes and onions.
Top with pork chops.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and continue baking 30 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and 1 teaspoon salt.
Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar and oil.
Mix until blended.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture.
Spread batter in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch cake pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: mars krispies
directions: Melt margarine and Mars bars or Snickers until creamy.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Pat into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut.
Serve. Great snack.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Brown ground meat.
Pour meat in baking dish.
Heat soups and water mixture.
Pour over meat.
Spread cheese over mixture. Cover with Tater Tots and bake at 350° until brown (about 1 hour). Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: homemade vegetable beef soup(crock-pot)
directions: In a heavy skillet over medium heat, brown the cubed round steak, using cooking oil or spray, if necessary.
In crock-pot, put together browned beef and Soup Starter according to package directions.
Allow to cook on low all day.
(To conserve time, brown the beef the night before and refrigerate.)
About 30 minutes before serving, add the bouillon cubes and canned vegetables.
Stir well and allow to heat thoroughly before serving.
Serve with hot rolls or corn bread.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package.
Be sure to mix until thick.
Whip in large mixer bowl.
Mix other ingredients; stir into pudding.
Put in a rectangular Pyrex dish in refrigerator several hours or overnight before serving.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Bring the water, garlic, olive oil, salt and pepper to a boil in the bottom of a steamer.
Place florets in steamer insert and cook until tender, about 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan. Serves 4.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, Karo and sugar well with mixer.
Add salt, vanilla, half and half and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into 1/2 gallon freezer and freeze until well frozen.

title: apple bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream together the sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with apple slices.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 325° for about 60 minutes. Cool and slice.

title: barbara's macaroon sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar, brown sugar, shortening, oleo and vanilla until well blended.
Beat in egg.
Lightly spoon in flour, potato flakes, soda and salt until thoroughly combined. Stir in coconut and nuts.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and flatten with sugared bottom of a glass.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: sticky buns
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Break each loaf into ten pieces. Dip in melted margarine then dip into cinnamon sugar mixture.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and add enough milk to make 1 cup liquid.
Mix all ingredients together and put into small greased loaf pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: dill bread
directions: Mix together.
Let rise one hour.
Punch down and put in greased loaf pan.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake at 400°, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: valomino bars
directions: Melt over heat the oleo, chocolate chips, marshmallows and peanut butter.
Add the Rice Krispies and peanuts. Stir together and spread in buttered pan.

title: lemon poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray spring-form pan (9 or 10-inch). Reserve 1/2 cup mix for topping.
Combine remaining mix, milk, oil and egg; stir until moistened.
Spread 2/3 batter in bottom of pan.
Spoon preserves and top with remaining batter.

title: salmon appetizers
directions: Drain salmon; remove any bones.
In a small bowl, combine salmon, cream cheese, salsa and parsley.
(Add cumin, if desired.) Spread about 2 tablespoons of salmon mixture over each tortilla. Roll each tortilla tightly and wrap individually with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Slice each tortilla into bite size pieces.
Yields about 48 appetizers.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with crisp vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in butter.
Mix together with remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnite.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: tennessee barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients and allow to set for 12 hours.

title: simple caramel rolls
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle walnuts in bottom of pan. Break 1 loaf of bread in small pieces and place over nuts. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, pudding and milk.
Pour over bread.
Break last loaf in small pieces and place over all other ingredients.
Let raise 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn rolls out on a wax paper covered cookie sheet.

title: instant pudding dessert
directions: Mix together the cookie crumbs and melted oleo.
Press into bottom of 9 x 12-inch cake dish.
Beat together the pudding mix and milk until thickened.
Add the ice cream; stir until smooth. Pour over the cookie crumb crust.
Crush the Heath bars and spread on top.
Put in freezer until ready to serve.
Cut into squares to serve.
May add Cool Whip on top, if desired.

title: roman chicken
directions: Cut up chicken into small chunks;
dredge in seasoned flour and brown in a skillet with a little hot oil (olive oil is best), turning once or twice.
While chicken browns, seed the peppers and cut in bite sized pieces.
Quarter the tomatoes.
After chicken is browned, add vegetables all at once followed by 1/2 to 1 cup wine; turn up fire and toss lightly until bubbling.
Cover and lower heat until vegetables are just done.
Serve over steamed rice. Simply delicious.

title: grilled steak with herb butter
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, stir all ingredients except butter and steaks.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until all liquid has evaporated (5 to 6 minutes).
Set aside and cool completely.
In small bowl, stir together butter and cooked, cooled herbs.
Place mixture on waxed paper; shape into 4-inch log.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: apache cheese bread
directions: Cut the top off the bread, reserving the top, and scoop out the inside.
Combine the remaining ingredients and mix well.
This will be a very stiff mixture.
Fill the bread with the cheese mixture, replace the bread top and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or tear and dip with the bread.

title: cottage pancakes
directions: Mix in blender until smooth.
Heat skillet.
Spray with cooking oil.
Drop batter onto skillet, using 1 tablespoon. Brown and turn.
Makes 21 pancakes.

title: homemade granola
directions: Preheat
oven

In a large bowl combine oats, almonds, coconut,
wheat
germ and salt.
Stir in milk and oil and mix
thoroughly.
Spread

a
wax-paper
lined shallow baking pan and bake, stirring occasionally for 1 hour or until golden. Stir
in
raisins.	Let
cool
and	store in airtight containers. Makes 7 1/2 cups.
(And it's delicious too!)

title: pork medallions in mustard sauce
directions: Sprinkle pork with salt and pepper.
Dust with flour.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Saute pork for 4 minutes on each side or until browned and cooked through.
Transfer to heated serving platter. Add wine to pan.
Bring to boil over high heat, stirring up browned bits.
Reduce for 1 minute, then stir in sour cream.
Heat mixture 2 minutes or until thickened.
Remove skillet from heat. Stir in mustard and basil.
Serve medallions with sauce.
Garnish with egg, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: mystery salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, then add jello dry.
Blend well together.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix together and pour over any crispy raw vegetables or your favorite salad.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in greased shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
Mix dry ingredients with melted butter until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Prepare early in the day or the night before as this tends to season better and keep refrigerated until shortly before ready to use.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Blend all ingredients, except pie filling, together until crumbly.
Pat half of mixture on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with cherry pie filling.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken.
Take off the bone.
Cut torta in squares; drop in boiling broth.
Cook about 20 minutes.

title: waverly dessert
directions: Mix crackers and oleo. Spread into 9 x 12-inch pan. Beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually add sugar. When peaks form, spread on cracker mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°. When cool, spread with lemon pie filling. Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: pink salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, add pineapple, juice and other ingredients. Fold in whipped cream.
Let set overnight. Serve on lettuce with Ritz crackers.

title: creamy mocha frosting
directions: Cream butter.
Combine sugar and cocoa and gradually add to butter, beating until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, beat until light and fluffy.
Spread between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Garnish with chocolate leaves, if desired.

title: cole slaw(kentucky fried chicken recipe)
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar, salt, oil and vinegar.
Mix well, then pour this over chopped cabbage, onions and carrots. Mix well.
Let chill overnight before serving.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Spread potatoes in shallow baking dish. Top with sour cream, bacon, cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: fried carrots, potatoes and onions
directions: Slice the carrots and potatoes thin. Cut up the onion fine. Put all ingredients in iron skillet and cook on low for about 20 minutes or until tender. Can also add leftover beef, pork or bacon when vegetables are almost done for a one dish meal.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
If mixture seems dry, add broth to suit.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake at 305° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla on medium speed for 3 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from the pan.
When cool, drizzle with a mixture of 1 cup confectioners sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla or 1 teaspoon rum and 2 to 3 tablespoons hot water.
(Add water 1 tablespoon at a time until right consistency.)

title: potato salad
directions: Boil the potatoes until you can put a fork in the potatoes easily.
Drain the water off the potatoes. Cut potatoes into small cubes.
Chop the celery fine. Chop 10 eggs into small pieces.
Add the celery salt and mayonnaise to the other ingredients.

title: melon-berry salad
directions: In large bowl, toss cantaloupe, honeydew and blueberries.
Add Raspberry-Apple Vinaigrette.
Toss until well combined.
Line serving bowl with chicory lettuce and melon-berry mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.
Toss again lightly just before serving.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Combine soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce; mix.
Add vegetables and marinate at least 24 hours.
Serve either hot or cold.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: bean casserole
directions: Prepare in Dutch kettle or large pot.
Brown bacon; drain grease.
Brown hamburger in same pot with onion; drain grease. Add ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and the liquid from the pork and beans.
Drain a little liquid off the other beans.
Add all beans to pot.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and onions until done.
Drain well.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with corn chips or Tostitos.

title: hearty hungarian goulash(crock-pot)
directions: In crock-pot, mix the ingredients.
Cook on low for 8 hours or more.
Pour over rice or noodles.

title: pasta salad bowl
directions: In jar with tight fitting lid, combine oil, lemon juice, salt, pepper, red peppers, garlic, chives, basil and dill.
Shake well until combined.
Cook pasta.
Drain and turn into a large salad bowl.
Add dressing and toss.
Meanwhile, prepare vegetables.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Melt butter, cheese and half and half.
Saute onions, mushrooms, parsley and shrimp briefly and then add to half and half mixture.
Meanwhile, cook vermicelli; drain.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan; mix everything together.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Beat in eggs.
Combine applesauce and soda; add to the creamed mixture with flour and spices.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
These are delicious served warm for breakfast.
If using cream cheese, add while creaming the sugar and margarine. I like to just cut a little chunk and insert into each muffin before baking.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Blend flour and milk until smooth.
Cook over low heat until thickened and boiling (this is the tricky part, take your time or it will scorch).
Cool to room temperature.
Cream butter (or margarine) and shortening.
Gradually add sugar and beat until completely dissolved.
Add vanilla.
Add the cooled flour and milk mixture a tablespoon at a time.
Beat at high speed until light and fluffy.

title: strawberry jello mold salad
directions: Mix boiling water with jello; stir until jello is completely dissolved.
Add frozen berries; stir until berries are thawed. Mix may start to thicken.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour 1/2 jello mix into mold that has been sprayed with Pam until mix is almost set.
To the remaining jello mix, add sour cream and Cool Whip; mix well.
Pour over portion in mold; let set until stiff.
Unmold jello on a plate; top with Cool Whip.
Makes a 4-cup mold.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream Crisco; add sugars and eggs, then dry ingredients.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
They brown quickly on bottom. Bake, cool, then freeze, if desired, in tightly covered containers.

title: anadama bread
directions: Stir the cornmeal very slowly into boiling water. When thoroughly mixed (no lumps), add shortening, molasses and salt. Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast, then flour. Add enough more flour if needed to make a stiff dough. Knead well and keep in warm place; let rise to more than double in bulk. Shape into 2 loaves. Let rise until light. Bake in hot oven at 400° for about 1 hour.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasonings (mixture will be thick).
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in greased muffin tins, press to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon meat mixture into biscuit lined cups.
Sprinkle with cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: elsie's pound cake
directions: In the large bowl of an electric mixer, beat together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
At medium speed beat in eggs, one at a time for 1 minute after each addition.
Beat in flour in 4 additions until blended each time.
Beat in vanilla and lemon juice.
Turn into a greased and floured 10-inch angel cake pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until a cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean, 1 hour.
Cool cake in pan on a wire rack for 5 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine the vegetables.
Whisk together the remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables, mixing thoroughly. Refrigerate.
Prepare the day before so the flavors will blend. This salad looks good in a glass bowl.
Serve at room temperature.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Make pastry and line 9-inch pie plate. Saute onions in butter or margarine until tender. Arrange on pastry. Beat eggs slightly; add evaporated milk, salt and pepper. Pour mixture over onions. Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes or until metal knife inserted in center comes out clean and pie is well browned. Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: pizza appetizer
directions: Press the rolls flat on a large cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Set aside to cool. Combine next 7 ingredients and spread mixture over cooled crescent roll.
Cut into small squares.
Cover with fresh vegetables of your choice.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over all and press down.

title: greek chicken
directions: Rub Cornish hens with butter and minced garlic.
(Rub so butter and garlic cover completely both inside and outside.)
Pour olive oil over hens, enough to coat well.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and black pepper.
(Be very generous with black pepper.) Bake in oven at 350° until golden brown.
Save liquid from pan when done.
Pour over green beans or boiled potatoes.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Brown together and drain the hamburg, bacon and onion. Mix together in a large casserole with the pork and beans, lima or butter beans, kidney beans, catsup, salt, brown sugar, vinegar and dry mustard.
After all ingredients are mixed together in a large casserole, bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Very good when reheated, too.

title: veal stew(beef may be substituted)
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces.
In a Dutch oven, saute onions in oil until opaque (clear).
In a plastic bag put flour, garlic powder, pepper, paprika and beef or veal cubes.
Shake until meat is coated with mixture.
Place in Dutch oven with onions.
Braise for about 20 minutes, stirring regularly until meat is browned.

title: lemon drop cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar and butter flavoring.
Add egg, vanilla and lemon flavoring; beat thoroughly.
Sift together the dry ingredients; add alternately to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
This is a rather soft dough.
Drop by scant teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, until edges are lightly browned.

title: food processor white bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water and let foam 3 to 5 minutes.
Combine flour, butter and salt in food processor; process about 20 seconds, until it is a coarse meal.

title: pork tenderloin with apricot sauce
directions: Combine 3/4 cup nectar, oil, 3 tablespoons teriyaki sauce and rosemary in a large shallow baking dish.
Add tenderloins, turning to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: five-cup salad
directions: You cut some oranges, cut bananas, cut apples and pick some grapes off stem.
Put some peach yogurt; stir it all up.
Put it in the refrigerator.
That's all.
Then you eat it.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Cook until smooth and pour over broccoli. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May sprinkle paprika on top after removing from oven.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Cut up 1 large onion fine, simmer in 1/8 pound butter until golden brown.
Add first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Shape into small balls and brown on all sides in hot oil.
Remove from oil and drain.
Place in deep frypan or Dutch oven.
Pour over 1/2 can chicken gravy diluted with 1/2 can water, 1/2 can of beef gravy diluted with 1/2 can water.
Slice 1 large onion in thick slices and lay these and celery across top of the meat balls.
Simmer meat balls for 30 to 35 minutes.
Discard onion and celery before serving.

title: cold fruit soup
directions: Cook fruits in 2 quarts of water.
Drain, reserving liquid. Put through strainer or in blender and cook briefly once again. Dissolve cornstarch (or tapioca) in 1/2 cup of water or fruit juice and add to liquid.
If tapioca is used, cook until it's transparent.
Flavor with sugar and lemon and possibly wine. Chill and serve cold.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.
Serves 8.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Dice and saute onion and peppers.
Flatten biscuits in a pie plate.
Put saute mix in pie shell.
Cover with tomatoes.
Cover tomatoes with mayonnaise.
Top with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° or until crust is brown.

title: black magic chocolate cake and frosting
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl; add shortening and hot coffee.
Blend; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition; add flavorings.
Pour into two 9-inch round pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and frost.

title: apple orchard cake
directions: Mix this recipe by hand.
Mix oil, sugar, eggs, soda, salt and vanilla flavoring.
Add flour and mix.
Add apples, pecans and coconut.
Bake in a tin pan at 300° for 1 hour, then 30 more minutes at 325° to brown it.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender.
Beat until creamy; add butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: stir-fry pork with spaghetti
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons
oil in a large frying pan and saute garlic and
red
pepper
flakes
for
29	seconds;
add
cold spaghetti (this is a great use for leftover spaghetti).
Saute to heat and set
aside.
In
a	hot
wok
(large frying pan is o.k.) add 4 tablespoons
oil and stir-fry pork for a minute or so.
Remove to a
separate
dish.	Reheat	wok
and
add
the veggies.
Stir-fry for
a minute, then add the stock and cover for
2 minutes	or so.
Uncover
and
add
the
Oyster
sauce (available
in
your local
grocery
in	the
Oriental
food section).
Return meat
to the pan.
Mix cornstarch and water and pour into
the
pan.
Stir until sauce thickens a little. Add the sesame oil and the spaghetti from the other pan.
Stir a little to mix and serve about 4 happy people.

title: chili with beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook for 1 hour in large boiler.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Put first five ingredients in a one-gallon freezer.
Fill with milk.
Fruit may be added, if desired.
Freeze.
(No eggs are required.)

title: peanut butter granola pizza
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey together.
Cover warm crust with the mix.
Sprinkle all other ingredients over the peanut butter and honey mix.
Put the cheese on last.
Return pan to oven and bake for about 10 minutes at 350°.
When the crust is light brown and crisp, it is done.
Slice it like a pizza and serve hot.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with caramel frosting or other favorite frosting.

title: pear crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray a 2-quart glass baking dish with vegetable oil spray.
Peel, core and slice pears and place in dish.
Toss pear slices with lemon juice, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a small bowl, combine flour and butter.
Using your fingertips, rub butter into flour until it resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in brown sugar and oatmeal.
Sprinkle over the top of the pears. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until pears are tender and top is browned.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: spinach elegante
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions. Drain well. Spread on bottom of 10 x 6 x 1/2-inch baking dish. Arrange bacon and mushrooms over spinach. Sprinkle with dash of pepper and marjoram. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Cover with sour cream and cheese. Return to oven 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Serves 6.

title: yogurt soup
directions: Place all
ingredients	in
blender container and blend until creamy smooth.
Chill before serving.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat then add first 3 ingredients plus salt and pepper.
Simmer
for 20 minutes.
Heat oil in skillet.
Cut 2 tortillas into quarters.
Brown until golden and crisp.
Set aside.
Cook and brown the remaining tortillas and break these up for chips.
Stir the hamburger meat mixture occasionally as you brown the tortillas. Combine the American cheese, cottage cheese, and egg in a bowl.
spread 1/3 of the meat mixture then 1/2 of the broken chips.
Repeat this ending up the the two quarter tortilla chips as a topping for the Mexican Lasagna.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let set for 5 minutes.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter in large bowl.
Add Seven-Up; cream until light and fluffy.
Be sure Seven-Up mixes in.
Add Crisco; cream again. Add sugar gradually; cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each addition.
Add vanilla, lemon extract and butter flavorings.
Gradually add flour to batter, blending thoroughly. Pour into prepared stem pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: greek butterball cookies
directions: Mix the flour, baking soda and almonds.
Set aside.
Heat butter slowly in a small deep saucepan.
Cool.
Carefully spoon off into a large bowl the clarified butter from top of cloudy solids which have settled at the bottom of the pan.

Add sugar, brandy, lemon juice, extract, oil and egg yolk to butter. Beat well. Add the flour-nut mixture in fourths, mixing thoroughly after each addition. Shape dough into 3/4-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at
350° for 15 minutes.

title: spinach salad(tasty combination - delicious dressing)
directions: In a 2 cup jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine the first 12 ingredients.
Shake well; set aside.
Wash spinach carefully, removing tough stems.
Drain (no need to dry).
In a large salad bowl, tear spinach into bite-size pieces.
Add mushrooms and reserved dressing; mix gently to distribute dressing well. Arrange salad on 6 serving plates; garnish with crumbled bacon and top with egg slices.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Combine cherry pie filling, pineapple and sugar.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, add bananas, marshmallows and pecans.

title: squash sonata
directions: Cook squash, onions and carrots in boiling salted water until tender; drain well.
Add soup and sour cream.
Drain pimentos; chop.
Add to squash mixture; stir well.
Mix butter and stuffing in greased casserole.
Add squash mixture.
Cover with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: baked apples(microwave)
directions: Put apples in microwave-proof dish. Arrange apples in dish. Combine cinnamon and sugar.
Fill center of each apple with 1/4 of the mixture.
Dot each with 1 teaspoon margarine.
Cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage cheese roll-up
directions: Heat cheese until just soft.
Spread Cheez Whiz on both sides of bread slices.
Cut bread into 4 or 5 inch pieces.
Roll sausage into Cheez Whiz covered bread and placed on greased baking sheet seam side down.
Bake until edges are lightly browned.
Leave long or cut in bite-sized pieces.
Can be frozen and reheated.
Bake at 325°.

title: yellow tail with bananas and vermouth
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash filet and pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour.
Place in buttered baking dish. Peel and slice banana lengthwise.
Arrange on top of fish.
Mix butter and vermouth.
Pour over fish.
Bake, basting often, for 20 to 25 minutes or until flaky.

title: ham soup
directions: Fry bacon, crumble and set aside.
Add onion to 2 tablespoons of the bacon drippings and cook until tender.
Add beef shank, ham, water and salt.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat from shank and dice.
Skim fat from soup.
Add beans, potatoes and garlic and simmer 30- minutes covered.
Add cut sausage, bacon and simmer 15 minutes.	Serves 10-12.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar and vanilla (mix).
Add zucchini with dry ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased (loaf) pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rum cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch or 9-inch cake pans.
Combine cake mix, eggs, 2/3 cup Bacardi rum and the water in large bowl; blend well.
Beat at medium mixer speed for 2 to 4 minutes.
Turn into prepared pans; bake according to package directions.
Cool layers thoroughly; split in half horizontally.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients for filling together, adding pecans last. Pour
into
9-inch
unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to
35 minutes
longer.
When
pie
is
done,
outer edges of filling should be set, center slightly soft.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Heat vegetable oil in 3-quart saucepan on medium until hot. Add onions and saute 1 to 2 minutes until translucent.
Add chili powder and saute for 1 minute.
Add the remainder of seasonings and mix well.
Add the chicken broth and stewed tomatoes and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: gourmet cheese cake
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar, cream cheese, flour, sour cream and lemon juice; beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites until frothy; add sugar gradually and continue beating until peaks form.
Fold into cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cool in oven for 1 hour.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix flour, butter, corn and cheese until melted.
Add cayenne pepper and cook until thickened.
Add egg yolks.
Let cool.
Add beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes in souffle dish.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients and cut into shortening until well mixed.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Roll on floured board and cut as for biscuits.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen. You may cook small amounts and store unused portions in refrigerator in a covered glass bowl.
Will keep about 2 weeks.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat. Add coconut and pecans. Pour over cake.

title: french fried apples
directions: Make a batter of eggs, sugar and flour.
Dip apple slices into batter and fry in oil until light brown.
Drain on paper towels. Dust with powdered sugar.
Great with sausage or bacon.

title: quick crescent taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, water and olives.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Separate crescent dough in 8 triangles. Place in ungreased pie pan, pressing to form crust.
Sprinkle 1 cup chips over bottom.
Spoon meat over chips, sour cream over meat and cover with cheese.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until brown.
Cut into servings and serve with shredded lettuce, diced tomato and salsa.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, and broth together and place in casserole dish. Melt margarine. Add milk and flour to margarine. Mix well and pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350 degrees until light brown and bubbly.

title: salisbury steak(microwave)
directions: You also need a browning dish.

title: donuts
directions: Mix well; roll out.

title: dump salad
directions: Sprinkle pudding from package over undrained pineapple and oranges that have been dumped into a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Chill.

title: betty's dill dip
directions: Put lemon juice in a blender.
Add other ingredients; blend on high until smooth, about 1 minute.
Makes 1 pint.
Serve on crackers, chips or raw vegetables.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix flour and 2 tablespoons brown sugar. Cut in 1/2 cup margarine.
Put in ungreased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Pat in pan for crust. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake bars
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar and spice together in mixing bowl. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix on top of mixture. Add chopped pecans. Layer cubes of butter on top. Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: deep-dish apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples. Mix sugar and cinnamon and place in 8 x 8 x 2 pan. Combine together ingredients and pat firmly in apples. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, margarine and chocolate chips together. Pour over cereal.
Stir well until coated.
Place powdered sugar in a plastic bag, along with coated cereal and shake well until coated with powdered sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and let cool and dry.

title: english salad
directions: Drain juice from all vegetables.
In a pan, mix salt, black pepper, sugar, oil, vinegar and water.
Mix and heat mixture, stirring until sugar has dissolved.
Remove from heat; let stand to cool.
After cooling, mix in with vegetables.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Pour marinade juice off.
Ready to serve.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Put all ingredients
in a large bowl and mix with hands until a smooth dough
is formed.	Shape into a ball; dust with flour and chill
thoroughly
before
using.
(Can
be left for several days.)
Break into conveniently sized pieces, probably adding a bit more
flour
to
each
piece
of dough to make it easier to handle.
Roll
out	as
thin as possible.
Dust with granulated sugar
and	nutmeg	or
colored sugar after cutting into desired shapes.
Bake
until
light
brown (6 minutes) at 300°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar together.
Roll quartered biscuits in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Grease and flour bundt pan.
Place quartered biscuits in pan. Melt butter, add sugar and 1 tsp. cinnamon together. Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake in preheated 375 degree oven for about 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: microwave baked potato
directions: Cooking Time:
For 1 potato, cook 3 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes.
For 2 potatoes, cook 6 to 8 minutes.
For 4 potatoes, cook 10 1/2 to 12 1/2 minutes.
Power Level:
High.

title: spaghetti
directions: Fry hamburger
in
frying pan.	Drain grease.
Add each ingredient	in
order,
stirring
in as you go.
Let cook over low heat, while you cook spaghetti noodles.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add morsels, and rest of ingredients. Put in jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sauerkraut carrot salad
directions: Add all ingredients to cut up sauerkraut.
Let stand 24 hours before serving.
Add and/or omit ingredients to suit taste and preference.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter in saucepan; add sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture gradually, mixing well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut in bars.
Makes 48.

title: baby food bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and baby food with mixer until well beaten.
Add remainder of ingredients and mix well.
Bake in three 1 pound coffee cans (well greased) at 350° for 1/2 hour; then reduce heat to 325° and bake for another 1/2 hour.
Cool in cans before removing.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly, fold in sugar, meal and flour. Add lemon juice and butter. Pour in pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: raisin date bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl, pour milk over bread.
Add sugar, eggs, butter, dates, raisins, vanilla, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg; stir to mix well.
Pour in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
If desired, sprinkle top with additional sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until golden brown and a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: eliza's corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; mix dry ingredients and add to eggs.
Add milk, cream, margarine and corn.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°, stirring after 15 minutes.

title: mostaccioli with tomato sauce
directions: In a large skillet, combine all ingredients as needed.
Cook beef until brown; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce and paste.
Put about 1 cup of water.
It needs to be thick tomato sauce.
Simmer sauce for 1/2 hour.
While sauce is simmering, boil water in a deep pan.
Add mostaccioli with 2 teaspoons salt so the mostaccioli won't stick.
Cook mostaccioli for 15 to 20 minutes. Drain.
Serve sauce over mostaccioli.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: 3-cheese quiche
directions: One pie crust shell baked at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: quick taco bake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion (drained).
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Stir in taco seasoning mix (dry), tomato sauce and whole corn.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Stir Bisquick (reduced fat or regular) baking mix, milk and eggs together.
Blend well and pour over beef mixture.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Boil syrup and sugar together for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 minutes. Remove from heat and add the rest of the ingredients. Drop by spoonful onto wax paper to cool.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Mix beans, hot sauce and onion together.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Form second layer.
Sprinkle with lettuce and shredded cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Add sugar, onion flakes, celery seed and vinegar to pickles; let stand at room temperature overnight.
Stir once or twice.
Put back in jar and refrigerate.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Dissolve onion soup mix in 1/4 cup hot water.
Add to mixture of Russian dressing and apricot preserves; set aside.
Arrange chicken pieces in pan and pour the sauce on top.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Add garnish of pineapple and green pepper. Bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and flour together. Add peaches, milk and margarine. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill at least 30 minutes.

title: hot spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.
Put 1 to 2 teaspoons mixture in cup and fill with hot water.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine ground beef, milk, catsup, crumbs, onion, salt, oregano and pepper.
Spread in unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Toss together cheese and Worcestershire; spread over meat.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tabasco green mayonnaise
directions: Blend all together and pour over tossed salad.

title: layered dip
directions: Mix all for a very fine dip for anything dippable.

title: cheese and ham strata
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cheese, ham and mustard.
Spread 1/2 cup ham mixture on 5 slices of toast.
Top with remaining slices.
Quarter sandwiches diagonally.
Arrange in 3 rows in a buttered long baking dish, standing crust side down.
Combine milk and eggs.
Pour over top and sides of sandwiches.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Place crumbled cake evenly in a cake pan.
Mix strawberries and glaze together.
Mix Dream Whip, sugar and cream cheese together.
Combine both mixtures.
Pour over cake.
Pour strawberries, evenly, on top.
Chill for an hour.

title: mounds bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Combine Eagle milk and coconut and spread over graham crust.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter and spread over mixture.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: seafood cracker dip
directions: In a blender, combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Remove from blender and mix in seafood.
Cover and chill.
Serve with non-fat saltine crackers.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: dump cake
directions: Place ingredients in a 9 x 13 pan in order that they are written down.
bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: cheese crabmeat sandwiches
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Heat cheese, if necessary for easy mixing and spread on muffins.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: tortellini minestrone(8 to 10 cups)
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, brown sausage.
Add next 7 ingredients. Bring to a boil; simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Skim any fat from soup.
Stir in zucchini, tortellini, green pepper and parsley. Simmer, covered, until pasta is tender, about 30 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir meat and onion in butter until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain a little; stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles and enjoy!

title: green gelatin salad
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package instructions.
Chill until beginning to get firm (about 1 hour).
Do not allow it to get completely firm.
Drain juice from pineapple into small saucepan.
Add marshmallows and melt completely in juice.
Mash cream cheese with a fork in a large bowl.
Add marshmallows and pineapple juice.
Add pineapple and mix thoroughly.
Add pecans. Whip cream until it begins to thicken, then add gelatin and whipped cream.
Mix together until well blended.
Pour into large (13 x 9-inch) glass pan and chill until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot tuna supreme
directions: Put tuna, peas and mushroom soup in microwave dish; microwave 5 minutes.
Place slice of bread, covered with slice of cheese, in plate.
Pour tuna, peas and soup over it.
Serves 4.

title: waldorf chicken salad
directions: Toss apples with lemon juice.
Mix chicken, celery, walnuts and raisins.
Add enough mayonnaise to hold salad together.
Can be served in hollowed out tomatoes, if desired.

title: tea time tassies
directions: Work the ingredients for the crust.
Chill 1 hour or overnight. Roll dough and cut into small circles and place in ungreased miniature cupcake tins.
Add about 1 teaspoonful of filling. (Optional:
You can top with a maraschino cherry.)
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan butter balls
directions: Combine flour, margarine, 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla, salt and pecans.
Mix with fork until well blended.
With lightly floured hands, shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in preheated oven at 325° for 20 minutes or until slightly brown on bottom.
Let cool a few minutes before removing from cookie sheet. Put confectioners sugar in plastic bag.
Shake until coated.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Grease loaf pan. Line bottom with waxed paper.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: seafood salad
directions: Bring noodles (shells) to a full boil.
Drain and chill before adding ingredients.
Mix in all ingredients with the noodles (shells) and chill 1/2 hour before serving.

title: caramel icing
directions: Put 4 tablespoons sugar in deep, heavy pot and brown.
Add butter and stir continually until sugar dissolves.
Set off of heat.
Add rest of sugar and cream.
Put back on stove and cook until it piles up (about 240°).
Cool and frost cake.

title: italian love cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
In separate bowl, combine Ricotta, sugar, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon over top of unbaked cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool. Mix pudding with milk; fold in whipped topping. Spread over cake; refrigerate.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in apples and nuts. Spread in greased pan (9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rice and beef deroma
directions: Salt and pepper pieces of top round steak, cut thin.*
Add sliced onion; roll meat to cover.
Add 1/2 slice bacon spread with mustard and roll meat to cover.
Continue to roll meat up and secure with toothpick, inserted horizontally.
Brown all sides in butter.
Add a very small amount of water; cover and lower heat to simmer until tender.
(I use a heavy Dutch oven and cook about 2 hours.)
Make a basic white sauce.
Remove beef from pan to serving dish; add sauce to gravy, cooking just enough to mix. Pour over the rolls of beef and serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick softened margarine with the crumbs.
Mix sugar, eggs and remaining margarine.
Beat until thick.
Spread over crumbs, sliced bananas (lengthwise).
Save a few slices for the top layer.
Spread pineapple (drained) over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip and decorate with cherries.
Sprinkle with nuts and chill for at least 8 hours.

title: ground beef and noodles
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add sour cream, onion soup mix and cream of chicken soup.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add noodles and heat thoroughly.

title: jello angel food cake
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
Pour into large bowl. Press 1 angel food cake into jello until all mixture has been absorbed.
The cake will seem to come to pieces.
When placed in refrigerator, cake will become solid.
Frost with 1 large container of Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak dry beans using 8 cups water.
Add the 1/2 teaspoon salt. Bring to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beans are tender, about 1 hour.
Drain, reserving bean liquid.
Combine molasses, brown sugar, the remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper. Stir in 2 cups of the reserved bean liquid.
In a 2-quart bean pot or casserole, combine cooked beans, ham, onion and molasses mixture.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 1/2 hours.
Stir beans occasionally.
Stir in a little of the reserved liquid or water for moistness if necessary.

title: the "ultimate" salad shrimp and grape with dill
directions: Bring 4 quarts salted water to a boil.
Drop in the shrimp. Wait 1 minute.
Empty the pot into a colander set in the sink. Let the shrimp cool in the colander.
Transfer the cooled shrimp to a bowl.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake the sweet potatoes in oven until you can put a toothpick through them.
Cream the potatoes while hot with butter.
Stir eggs in the sugar.
Add a teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: western mac
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed.
Brown meat, celery, green pepper and onion; cook until tender.
Stir in corn, tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Add dinner; mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Saute bacon, hamburger and chopped onion in a large pan.
Add remaining ingredients and bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° or in crock-pot.

title: party punch
directions: Combine fruit juice, add 1 bottle of 7-UP, add sherbet.
Pour remaining bottle of 7-UP over sherbet.

title: tarragon chicken salad
directions: Arrange chicken breast in single layer in large jelly roll pan.
Spread evenly with heavy cream and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Shred meat into bite size pieces and transfer to bowl.
Whisk sour cream and mayo together in small bowl and pour over chicken.
Add celery, walnuts, tarragon, salt and pepper. Toss well.
Refrigerate covered at least 4 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican style scrambled eggs for 30 people
directions: Break eggs into a large bowl and beat with fork or egg beater. Add the chopped vegetables, mushrooms, and meat; add seasonings to taste. Heat oil in large skillet. Cook the egg mixture to scramble.

title: 7-up punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except 7-UP real well (may use blender) and freeze.
When ready to serve, get out of freezer and let partly thaw.
Then add 7-Up to punch and serve.
Serves about 30 people.

title: my hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground
beef in skillet.
While browning, stir in onions; salt and pepper
to
season.
Mix
and
prepare mashed potatoes; set aside.
When beef
is
done, drain fat.
Mix the corn and tomato soup
into
beef.
Transfer to casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese over beef
mixture.
Top with mashed potatoes. Bake at 350° for 35 to
minutes.
Let
cool for 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 5 to 6 guests.

title: emily thompson's creamy broccoli casserole
directions: *May use 1/2 corn.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes; cook until done, but firm, about 20 minutes. Drain.
Quarter potatoes, then cut into medium size pieces.
Mix the pickles, relish, mustard and mayonnaise.
Taste and add additional ingredients as needed.
Just before you serve the salad, toss potatoes gently in with the other ingredients, the chopped pepper and onion.

title: taco salad
directions: Arrange in order as written, using a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: special lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Add tomato sauce, spices and mushrooms. Simmer on low. Boil pasta until tender and drain. Mix eggs, parsley and Parmesan cheese (should be like a paste). Spray 9 x 13 casserole dish with Pam. Layer pasta, then egg mixture and then Mozzarella cheese. Layer pasta, egg and cheese again. Final layer should be pasta. Cover with tinfoil and bake in oven at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve by taking a portion of pasta dish and topping with sauce mixture. Cheese in every bite.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and boil with sliced onion until done.
Drain and add salt, pepper and margarine.
Layer in dish: 1/2 squash mixture, 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup and cheese.
Repeat with next layer.
Top with crushed saltines.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ground beef pasta bake(one dish dinner)
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions. Drain.
Reserve liquid.
Set spinach aside.
Add enough water to liquid to make 1 cup; set aside.

Cook ground chuck, onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil in a large skillet, stirring until meat crumbles and onion is tender. Drain; discard liquid. Add 1 cup spinach liquid, spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce and paste, salt and pepper to beef in skillet.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Set aside.
Cook pasta as package directs. Drain.
Combine pasta, spinach, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, eggs and 1 tablespoon oil.
Divide pasta mixture in two 8-inch square baking dishes. Spoon sauce evenly over pasta. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle casseroles evenly with rest of cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes.
Yields 4 servings per casserole.

title: ginger pork
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put pork in pan; sprinkle with salt, pepper, rosemary and ginger.
Pour 1 cup of wine in pan.
Cook and bake 1 hour.
Remove pan from oven.
Place marmalade in small bowl.
Add pan drippings; mix well.
Pour over meat.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes, basting meat.
Serve pork with pan juices.

title: chicken and peaches
directions: Cut and clean chicken.
Coat with Shake 'n Bake per package instructions.
Place on foil in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover and pour entire can of peaches over chicken.
Place, uncovered, in oven for another 20 minutes.

title: herb peel away bread
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
Combine 2 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast, cheese and herbs.
Heat water and 4 tablespoons butter until hot to touch (125° to 130°).
Stir into dry mixture.
Stir in egg and only enough flour to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 4 minutes, on lightly floured surface. Cover and let rest 10 minutes.

title: chicken cashew
directions: Brown chicken in butter and oil.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
In the browning pan, add remaining ingredients except paprika.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve with rice and garnish with cashews and mushrooms (optional).

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Place margarine and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat and add stuffing mix, tossing lightly until croutons are thoroughly moistened.
Fill pork chops with stuffing; fasten edges with wooden toothpicks.
Place flat side down in single layer in shallow baking pan.
Do not crowd.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Make crust in 9 x 13 pan.
Beat 2 sticks margarine, sugar and eggs together (at least 15 minutes).
Spread filling over crust.
Drain pineapple and layer over filling.
Slice bananas over pineapple. Cover with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and cherries. Refrigerate.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add crackers; set aside.
Mix beans, onion, soup and cheese to taste.
Pour into baking dish and top with some more cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot, about 20 minutes.

title: pecan and raisin cake
directions: Mix pecans and raisins in a big bowl.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Pour dry mixture over pecans and raisins.
Beat egg yolks.
Add vanilla and mix well into flour and nuts.
Fold stiffly beaten egg whites in.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: In a heavy 6-quart Dutch oven, heat the oil over low heat for 1 minute; add onion, carrot, garlic and green pepper and cook, covered, for 10 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
Add lentils, chili powder, cumin, bay leaf, cayenne pepper and tomatoes, along with a small amount of water if it seems thick. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add chickpeas, black beans and pinto beans.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or more, until lentils are tender.
Serves 4.
Good served over rice.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
Cooking:
50 minutes.

title: humboltd pecan pie
directions: Mix the egg yolks, sour cream, cornstarch, lemon rind and salt in top of double boiler and cook over boiling water until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat the egg whites until stiff, adding brown sugar slowly.
Fold in pecans and spread over filling.
Bake at 425° until lightly brown. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: cornmeal stuffing
directions: Heat broth to boiling.	Gradually add cornmeal, stirring constantly.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add bread, celery, onions, poultry seasoning and egg.	Season to taste.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in pan at 350° or stuff in cavity of bird and bake until brown.

title: strawberry glazed pie
directions: Line pie shell with all except 1 cup of berries (standing tip side up looks pretty).
Simmer 1 cup of berries in water 3 to 4 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients and add slowly to cooked berries.
Cook again until thickened and clear.
Remove from heat. Add lemon juice.
Pour over berries in pie shell.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Lay bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chopped chicken pieces.
Mix together other ingredients and pour over top of chicken.
Put slices of cheese over mixture and pour 2 cans of undiluted cream of chicken soup.
Top with bread crumbs.
Cover and refrigerate overnight for a better flavor.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 10.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: If using an electric mixer, add dry ingredients to liquid. Grease 2 loaf pans and fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meatballs
directions: Make enough meatballs using your favorite recipe or frozen (bought in grocery store) to fill a crock-pot.
Mix currant jelly and chili sauce together.
Pour over meatballs.
Heat through.

title: barbecue dip
directions: Put all ingredients into blender; mix until smooth.
Serve hot or cold with chips or other dippable food.

title: pie crust(makes enough for 5 or 6 crusts)
directions: Blend flour, baking powder, salt, and Crisco.
Beat egg and vinegar and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Mix together all ingredients.
Make into 5 or 6 balls and freeze until ready to use.

title: salad supreme
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Chill until partially set; top with crushed pineapple and first 1/2 cup pecans.
Combine whipped topping and cream cheese.
Spread mixture over pineapple layer and chill.
Combine reserved juice, lemon juice, sugar, flour and eggs in small saucepan.
Cook over low flame until thickened.
Chill thoroughly; spread over top. Sprinkle with second 1/2 cup chopped pecans, if desired. Return to refrigerator until served.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken in enough water to cover with salt, onions, celery and carrots until tender, about 1 hour.
Remove chicken from bones and cut into large chunks.

title: frito salad
directions: In a 9 x 13 dish, spread 3/4 bag of Fritos.
Heat chili and pour over Fritos.
Layer lettuce and tomato.
Spread rest of Fritos.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Pour dressing over all.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add Veg-All, water and tomatoes. Add bay leaf.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add macaroni.
Stir and cook until macaroni is done.
Add ketchup and salt and pepper to taste. Remove bay leaf.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pudding, then add dry mix in and mix together. Refrigerate.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together into mixing bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, egg and milk.
Mix together with blending fork or pastry blender just until ingredients are blended.
Blend in carefully the blueberries.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake until golden brown at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: banana parfait pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water in large bowl.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Then chill and thicken, but not set.
Fold in bananas.
Turn into pie shell.
Chill until firm.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add 4x sugar.
Gradually mix until not crumbly.
Shape to desired shape.
Let stand 12 hours at room temperature.
Coat with chocolate.

title: oven-fried honey chicken
directions: In shallow bowl, whisk together honey and vinegar. Pour bread crumbs into separate bowl; set bowls aside. Spread oil over foil-lined baking pan large enough to hold all chicken pieces in 1 layer. Roll chicken pieces in honey mixture, then in bread crumbs; place in pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until cooked through. Makes 4 servings.

title: sunshine slushes
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Let cool.
Mash bananas and add to all juices.
Add the sugar water and rum.
Stir.
Freeze.
When frozen, fill glass with slush.
Fill with 7-Up.

title: blonde brownies *
directions: Melt butter or oleo.
Add brown sugar.
Cook over low heat until it bubbles up.
Cool.
Add 2 eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 25 minutes.
While warm, cut into squares.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: savory fish fillets(quick and healthy)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Brush both sides of 1 pound flounder fillets.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes until fish flakes easily.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fish fry
directions: Cut fish into equal sizes so it all cooks in the same amount of time.
Salt and pepper fish.
Dip into egg, then into corn flakes.
Drop into hot oil and cook until golden.
Best to dry fish with soft cloth or paper towel before dipping.

title: tora's banana bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into dry mixture.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour one large or two medium-size loaf pans.
Fill with dough.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May cover with foil to prevent overbrowning.
Remove foil and continue baking until done.
(May be an additional 30 minutes for a large loaf.)

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and then add mayo and water. Use 2 (8-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will need 8 to 10 paper or plastic (8 ounce) cups, silk or plastic flowers, candy worms, frogs or bugs (if you wish).

title: skillet chops 'n beans
directions: Brown chops in skillet. Top each with a slice of onion. Season with salt and pepper. Cover and cook over low heat 45 minutes or until tender.
Push chops to one side. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook 5 minutes. Stir now and then.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in shortening; drain off excess fat.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add green pepper; cover and simmer another 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Add peanut butter and let cool.
Add Crispix cereal.
Stir until all cereal is coated.
Put confectioners sugar in trash bag.
Add cereal mixture and shake well.

title: gerry's five bean casserole
directions: Fry Italian sausage and drain off fat. Drain all the cans of beans except the pork and beans. Throw everything together in your crock-pot and mix well. Cook for a couple of hours or whatever (use low setting for whatever and keep checking so it doesn't get dry). Then, it's done.

title: mother's "corn likker" fruit cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually, and continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Add unbeaten egg whites, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder together. Alternately add flour and corn whiskey.
Blend well.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with desired amount of pie filling. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: baked crab cakes
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine or butter; do not brown. Cool completely.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mustard, paprika, mayonnaise and egg; mix well.
Gently fold in crab meat.
Shape into patties and coat with cracker crumbs.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and refrigerate 1 or 2 hours.
Bake in preheated 450° oven until lightly browned.

title: shrimp pudding
directions: Arrange 6 slices of bread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; remove crusts from bread.
Add half of shrimp and cheese.
Make another layer of bread, shrimp and cheese.
Combine eggs, soup, milk and pepper.
Pour evenly over casserole.
Let stand at least 15 minutes.
Several hours improves flavor.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli cuts according to directions.
Drain.
In a small bowl combine soup, milk and soy sauce.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole layer half of the broccoli, half soup and 1/2 French fried onions.
Top with rest of broccoli and soup mix.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Add remaining onions and bake 5 minutes more.
tags: cream of broccoli soup or mushroom

title: yum yum salad
directions: In a pot on top of stove add pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add the gelatine which has been dissolved in the orange juice.
Remove from stove and chill until partially set.
Add cheese, marshmallows and whipped cream.
Chill.

title: chile verde(chee-lay vair-day)
directions: Cut pork or beef into small cubes; put in large pan. Brown a little, then add the rest of the recipe. Cook over low heat until real tender. Cut most of the fat off of meat before cooking. This is excellent in burritos or over top of rice.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together broken pretzels, melted butter and sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400°
for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: stir-fry vegetables with tofu
directions: Place tofu in shallow bowl.
Mix soy, vinegar, cumin, garlic and ginger; drizzle this over tofu and set aside.
Heat oil in wok or large pan over high heat.
Add carrot and stir-fry 1 minute. Add broccoli and cook 2 minutes, then add mushrooms and onions. Reduce heat to medium.
Add tofu mixture and cook, stirring gently until heated through but vegetables are still crisp.
Garnish with cilantro.
Spoon over hot rice and pass the soy sauce and add crispy noodles on top.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 3 layers.

Drain pineapple; use juice with 1 1/2 cups sugar and cook to "spin a thread" stage. Pour 1/2 of this syrup into beaten egg white, beating constantly. Then use remaining 1/2 syrup, adding pineapple and cook until it thickens slightly.
Spread cooked pineapple mixture between layers of cake (slicing bananas onto pineapple between layers if desired).
Spread beaten egg white icing over top and sides of cake. Sprinkle with Angel Flake coconut, if desired.

title: miller popcorn balls
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil, except vanilla.	Boil to soft ball
stage.
Add
vanilla.
Pour
over
1 gallon popped corn. Let set a minute.
Using wet hands, form into balls.

title: reuben loaf
directions: In mixing bowl, combine 2 1/4 cups flour, yeast, sugar, butter and salt.
Stir in warm water and mix until a soft dough forms. Add remaining flour, if necessary.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth, about 4 minutes.
On a lightly greased baking sheet, roll dough to a 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread dressing down the middle of one-half of dough, leaving 3/4-inch space along edges.
Top with layers of beef, cheese and sauerkraut.
Fold the remaining half of dough over the meat mixture.
