Pinch edges together to seal.
Cut small slits in the dough to vent steam.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: 3 weeks bran muffin mix
directions: Pour boiling water over Nabisco Bran cereal and cool.
Hand mix in bowl the sugar, shortening, eggs, buttermilk, flour, salt, soda and Kellogg's Bran.
Now add everything together.
Bake in muffin tins or papers.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: aunt judy's angel food cake
directions: Break up cake in small pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over cake.
Mix together Dream Whip and spread over cream cheese and cake.
Spread pie filling over top.
Can top with a little whipped cream.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Combine beef and onion in a Dutch oven; cook until beef is browned.
Stir until it crumbles.
Drain.
Add beans and next 4 ingredients.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Refrigerate unless serving immediately. To serve, sprinkle with cheese.
Yield:
3 2/3 cups.

title: "trash"
directions: Will also need 1 tall plastic kitchen trash bag.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: hamburger and cabbage
directions: Brown onion and hamburg.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until tender, stirring several times.

title: top of the world pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Take off heat and add raspberry jello.
Cool and add bananas and nuts. Pour into baked pie shell.
Makes 2 or 3 pies.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together real well.
Bake 1 hour in 400° oven which has been preheated.

title: double apricot gelatin salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water, stirring until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and beat with mixer thoroughly.
Mix in water or juice and apricot halves.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add sour cream.
Add 1 cup flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture.
Add remaining flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Bake in 4 layers for 25 minutes at 350° or in a tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: killer punch(excellent for shower)
directions: Pour in large punch bowl with ice and slices of lime, lemon and maraschino cherries.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Add enough cold water to reserved pineapple juice to make a cup.
Add to jello mixture. Chill until soft set.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with soda.
Combine butter, sugars and vanilla pudding.
Mix in large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips. The amount of chips is your choice.
Add nuts or raisins, if desired.
Bake at 375° or 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oreo surprise
directions: Crush cookies; mix with melted margarine.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice ice cream; lay on top of cookies.
Stick in freezer for 5 minutes.
Put fudge topping over ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip and cherries.
Sprinkle with a little crushed cookie.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Make a long, narrow loaf.
Place meat loaf on top of 1 pound can of stewed tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexicali pork steaks
directions: Cut pork in serving size pieces, brown in large skillet.
stir in seasoning mix, tomatoes, & water cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. stir in rice, cook 30 minutes longer. Garnish with sliced olives.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt butter on low heat in top of a double boiler.
Add caramels; put lid on pot.
Stir occasionally.
Butter will be hard to get mixed with caramels, but don't give up.
Stir in nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto well greased waxed paper.
Cool until firm. Melt chocolate and paraffin on very low heat; dip caramels and nuts into chocolate mixture.

title: dazzling fruit tray
directions: Arrange fruits on large platter.
Sprinkle entire arrangement with dry Jell-O.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Mix egg white, vanilla, flour and milk.
Add Crisco, 10x sugar and peanut butter.
Beat until fluffy.

title: sun-dried tomato dip
directions: Puree the tomatoes, cream cheese, sour cream, mayo, Tabasco, salt and pepper in food processor. Add the scallions and pulse twice. Serve at room temperature with crudit or crackers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers and onions with salt and ice.
Mix and let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Heat to a boil and seal in jars.
Yield:
8 pints.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together cornstarch, sugar and salt. Cream in small amount of lemon juice. Add egg yolks; cream well. Add boiling water and mix well. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue, bake in 300° oven 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: cheeseburger broiled dinner
directions: Set oven to broil.
Mix ground beef, crumbs, salt, steak sauce and tomato juice.
Lightly form into 4 thick patties; place on broiler pan rack.
Arrange potatoes beside meat; dot with butter and sprinkle with pepper and seasoned salt.
Broil about 4 inches from heat until patties are browned (3 to 5 minutes); turn.
Again dot potatoes with butter; place tomato halves on rack beside potatoes.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes longer, until meat is browned. Cover each pattie with an onion slice; top with a slice of cheese. Broil until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Cook sugar, water and juice to soft-ball stage.
Add pecans and stir to coat.
Spread out to cool.

title: shrimp ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Bring soup to boil and dissolve cream cheese in it.
Dissolve gelatin in soup mixture and let cool.

title: easy icing
directions: Sift the sugar into the small bowl.
Add water, a little at a time, mixing it with the sugar to make a smooth paste.
To make chocolate icing, use 3 ounces sugar and the cocoa powder.
Make it the same way as the white icing.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix whipped topping and pudding mix together; mix well.
Add pineapple, nuts and cherries; mix real good and refrigerate.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Sweeten to taste.
Cook blackberries until they come to a boil. Add as much or as little as you want, and then add butter. Cook until thick.
Roll out the dough, cut as for biscuits and drop into the blackberries.
Then roll some dough thin, cut into strips and place on top of the blackberries.
Set the pan in oven until crust is brown.
Bake at 400°.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Rinse chicken; put in a large pot and cover with water.
Cook chicken until tender; remove from water.
Let cool.
Scrape scum from pot of water.
Add soups and bring to a full boil.
Cut up biscuits in quarters.
Plop into boiling soup.
Keep stuffing them into the pot.
Let cook 15 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently. Debone chicken and add to cooked dumplings.
Thicken if needed.

title: easy macaroons
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly, remove to cooling rack.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry kiss
directions: Pour cranberry juice and orange juice into a glass with ice. Top with club soda.
Garnish with orange twist.
Makes 1 serving.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: In blender, blend mayonnaise, milk, preserves, curry powder and salt. Pour over chicken, grapes, celery mixture. Cover and chill. Place chicken mixture on center of platter lined with lettuce. Slice cantaloupe around salad. Top salad with coarsely chopped walnuts.

title: meatball soup
directions: Season beef with salt and pepper; shape into 18 meatballs. In saucepan, brown meatballs (use shortening if necessary); cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup and water. Heat; stir now and then.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: kool-aid sherbet
directions: Dissolve sugar and Kool-Aid in milk. Pour into freezer tray. Freeze until partially firm. Spoon into cold bowl and beat with egg beater until smooth but not melted. Return to tray about 2 hours. Makes 3/4 quart.

title: french jam pie
directions: Line 8-inch pan with pastry and flute edges.
Spread jam onto crust.

title: diabetic fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Serve with favorite fruits.

title: orange salad
directions: Add Jell-O to Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Fold in orange slices and pineapple.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: lemon pecan fruitcake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine until smooth; add beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Combine 2 cups flour and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture.
Then add lemon extract.
Coat pecans, pineapple and cherries with remaining 2 cups flour and add to creamed mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Cover and let stand overnight.

title: oatmeal raisin bread
directions: Cover raisins with hot or boiling water and pour 4 cups hot or boiling water over oatmeal and let stand until lukewarm.
Use 1 cup of the lukewarm raisin water, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 cup flour and yeast and let stand 10 minutes.
Into the oatmeal, add 1/2 cup sugar, salt, vegetable oil and drained raisins.
Add yeast mixture and start working in the sifted flour.
The dough should be moist, almost sticky.
Place in greased large bowl.
Cover with warm damp towel and place in warm place to rise.
When doubled, knead down and let rise again.
Make into 4 loaves.
Let rise until doubled (or above pan edges).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Cut roll cookies in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cheese mixture over this.
Top with 1/4-inch sliced cookies from the second roll.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool completely and cut in squares.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chili mix
directions: Add mix to one pound of hamburger while browning.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Saute onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add beef and mix well.
Set aside.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain well.
Add margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs. Pour spaghetti into long cake pan or 2 pie pans, forming "crust". Spread Mozzarella cheese over crust, leaving 1/2-inch of spaghetti showing around the edge.
Pour meat mixture over cheese and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella over pie and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: hawaiian holiday
directions: Mix pineapple juice, pineapple and cream of coconut.
Serve over ice cubes in tall glasses.
Serves 4.

title: hobnail cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add egg and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir them in, a little at a time, and beat well.
Fold in raisins.
Form into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Check bottoms.

title: chicken liver stroganoff
directions: Place butter, onion and mushrooms in 2-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, until onion and mushrooms are tender.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Stir in flour, paprika, salt and pepper. Cut each chicken liver in half.
Add livers to mushrooms and onions.
Cook, covered, on Full power for 6 to 9 minutes or until livers are cooked.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Spoon sour cream over livers.
Cook on Full power for 30 to 60 seconds, until heated through, but not boiling.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream sugar and shortening together. Add eggs. Add flour, salt and baking soda. Add bananas and nuts. Bake 30 to 45 minutes in two greased and floured loaf pans.

title: oven roasted chicken and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking dish with 1 tablespoon of oil.
Toss chicken and potatoes with the remaining 2 tablespoons of oil.
Arrange in dish in an even layer.
Sprinkle with garlic, rosemary and 4 tablespoons lemon juice.
Cover loosely with foil. Bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer, turning chicken and potatoes.
Pour remaining lemon juice over chicken. Serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: gooey coffee cake
directions: With wooden spoon mix cake mix, eggs and melted oleo. Spread in a baking pan.
Do not grease pan.
A glass pan works well. Beat cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar until smooth. Spread over cake dough in pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°, sprinkle with 1/4 cup confectioners sugar when cake is cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook
hen.
Debone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook spaghetti;
drain.
Combine chicken and spaghetti with all the ingredients except the cheese.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
A great dish to freeze and cook when needed.

title: chantilly fruit
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and oranges; mix together.
Add small diced apple and sliced banana.
Mix Cool Whip with sour cream, vanilla and sugar.
Toss with fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Mix sour cream and next 7 ingredients.
Marinate chicken breasts 4 hours or, preferably, overnight.
Before baking, roll each piece in fine bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish.
Dot with plenty of butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. May cover when completely baked and turn oven to warm.
Will hold 2 hours with no harm to flavor.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Pour in baking dish.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Microwave spinach until partially cooked.
Mix spinach, soup, cheeses, garlic, oregano and mushrooms together in large bowl. Cook shells; drain and stuff with spinach mixture.
Brown hamburger; add sauce.

title: no-fat no-cholesterol dessert
directions: Layer as follows:
Crumble up loaf cake (not too small) in bottom of trifle dish or glass bowl.
Sprinkle with brandy or rum (optional).
Spread on raspberry (or any flavor) preserves. Spread on chocolate pudding.
Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip (8 ounce).
Add chocolate sprinkles (optional).

title: mexican bean dip
directions: On a cookie sheet or large decorative flat plate, spread refried beans.
In a small bowl, mix sour cream, taco seasoning mix and mayonnaise; spread over beans.
Top with cheese, then tomato, green onions and olives (or other toppings of your choice).
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Dip up with plain flavored nacho chips.

title: meal in a foil
directions: Tear 4 pieces of foil large enough to enclose hamburger and vegetables.
Place a hamburger patty on each piece of foil.
Add 1 slice onion, quartered potato and 1 sliced carrot.
Top each with 1 tablespoon of butter.
Season to taste.
Pull foil together; fold on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serve hot by sliding meat and vegetables onto plate.

title: spiced applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, applesauce and spices.
Mix well. Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool completely. Frost as desired.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in food processor.
Add lemon juice and seasonings to taste.
Combine yogurt, mayonnaise and 1 package taco seasoning mix.
Mix refried beans, chilies and 1 package taco seasoning mix.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Mix together and pack in a pan lined with wax paper.
This cake keeps well and can be made well before you plan to serve it.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
If using butter, margarine or shortening, melt over low heat.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar until blended.
Cool.
If using oil, just blend oil and sugar.
Stir in egg.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt together; blend in.
Mix in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in well-greased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake 25 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Cut in bars while warm.
Makes 18 bars, about 2 1/2 x 1-inch.

title: which came first pie
directions: Layer chicken over bottom of pie crust, then layer peas and carrots.
Add sliced eggs.
Sprinkle onion, salt and pepper over egg layer.
In a saucepan, blend milk and soup; heat to boiling. Pour over egg layer.
Mix margarine and stuffing together; pat evenly over top of pie.
Bake, covered, in a 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Uncover; continue baking until brown.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: dorothy's meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, onion soup mix and eggs; make into meatballs.
Combine in saucepan the cranberry sauce, chili sauce, water, brown sugar and sauerkraut for 30 minutes.
Pour sauce mixture over meatballs (use a 9 x 12-inch glass pan).
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: italian chicken
directions: Pour pizza sauce over chicken breasts.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve over spaghetti noodles or angel hair.

title: light 'n lean lasagna
directions: In large bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta or cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Combine eggs, thyme, basil, nutmeg and pepper; beat slightly.
Pour into spinach-cheese mixture and mix well.
Set aside.

title: morning brunch
directions: Place croutons in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place cheese on top.
Beat together sausage, eggs, mustard and 2 1/2 cups milk.
Pour beaten ingredients into dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over the top in the a.m.
Bake at 300° until it bubbles.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Melt and mix together the butter, mustard and tarragon.
Dip chicken in mixture, turning to coat all sides.
Mix crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley and cayenne.
Dredge chicken, one piece at a time, in crumb mixture, patting with hands to coat.
Arrange chicken in single layer in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: heaven bound casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oleo until transparent.
Add ground beef and brown until beef loses "pink" (drain off grease). Cook noodles according to directions and drain.
While noodles cook, mix soup, sour cream, mushrooms and olives until well blended.
Mix in ground beef well and add noodles.
Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish which has been greased with butter or sprayed with Pam.
Top with almonds (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until bubbly.
Can be made day before, then baked.
Leftovers freeze well.

title: cherry tomato salad(serves 6.  preparation time: 20 minutes.)
directions: Wash and stem tomatoes.
Dry completely.
Cook bacon until very crisp; drain thoroughly on paper towels.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, olive oil, salt and basil.
Pour over tomatoes, crumble bacon over all and stir to coat tomatoes with dressing.
Serve on lettuce leaves, sprinkled with chives.
Serve at once or refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cajun black beans and rice
directions: Chop onion coarsely.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil for 2 to 3 minutes (do not overcook onion).
Add drained and rinsed beans and Cajun seasoning; cook to heat only.
Add tomatoes, cilantro and salsa; combine with cooked rice.
Enjoy!

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar; put in boiler and bring to a boil, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk and fold in topping and pecans.
Chill until firm and cut into squares.

title: blue ribbon blueberry coffeecake
directions: Grease and flour 10 x 4 1/2-inch tube pan without removable bottom.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Over a small bowl sift 3 cups flour with the baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.

Put brown sugar, 1 tablespoon flour and cinnamon in medium bowl; mix well. In large bowl put butter and beat at medium speed until smooth. Add sugar and vanilla to the butter and beat until the mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, to the butter mixture, beating well after each.
Add flour mixture in 3 additions alternately with the sour cream (in 2 additions).
Be sure you beat batter thoroughly after each addition and scrape sides of bowl. Gently dust blueberries with 1 tablespoon flour.
Turn 1/3 of the batter into the prepared pan, spreading it evenly.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of blueberries and 1/2 of brown sugar-flour mixture.
Repeat layering of remaining batter, blueberries and brown sugar mixture. Bake for 60 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 20 minutes.
Mix confectioners sugar and milk, drizzle over cake.

title: fried green onions
directions: Cook bacon in skillet, remove bacon and add green onions, cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in milk and add to onion mixture.
Cook until thick and season to taste.
This is excellent with cornbread.

title: pinwheels
directions: Blend 1/2 cup butter, flour, salt and water until dough crumbles.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick, about 12-inch squares. Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Brush dough with 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over dough.
Roll and wrap in wax paper.
Chill about 3 hours.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: party salmon balls
directions: Drain salmon.
Mix with ingredients. Chill several hours. Combine 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 3 tablespoons chopped parsley. Shape into balls and roll in nuts and parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Slice cabbage in 1-inch strips and boil in salted water until tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken and prepare stuffing as directed.
Melt 4 slices American cheese in mushroom soup.
Lay chicken in dish and pour mushroom soup mixture over it and put stuffing on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fast-frozen salad(children's)
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Freeze in the freezer until firm.
Remove from freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: mexican salad
directions: Drain can of Ranch Style beans.
Marinate beans and chopped onion and celery in 1 bottle of dressing overnight in refrigerator.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and sprinkle potato chips evenly on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry egg in flat pan; do not stir.
Flip over until cooked. Slice into 1-inch strips.
Set aside.
Saute onion until clear; add meat.
Add to egg.

title: grandma's ice creamroswell, new mexico
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.

title: onion pie
directions: Combine crackers and 1/2 cup melted margarine to make a crust; line a shallow casserole dish.
Saute onions and 1/4 cup margarine until brown.
Put onions on top of cracker crust.
Sprinkle cheese on top of onions.
(This can be fixed hours ahead.)

title: french fried cheese
directions: If using a soft cheese, use as much of the crust as possible. Dip the cheese cube in egg, then in crumbs and repeat.
A thick coating helps keep the cheese from leaking through.
Heat oil to 375° and fry the breaded cheese about 30 seconds.
Cool slightly before eating.

title: farfel kugel *
directions: Scald farfel with water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add fat, salt and pepper and eggs.
Fold together.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan preheated with 3 to 4 tablespoons fat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
Light and fluffy, about 8 servings.

title: bombay chicken salad
directions: Combine and chill rice, onion, vinegar, salad oil and curry powder.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables.
Mix vinegar, oil and sugar and pour over vegetables and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Mix together in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve with crackers.

title: my moist meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well until blended.
Place in loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with bacon or baste with broth or hot water.

title: crunchy brown rice
directions: Combine stock or broth and green onions in saucepan.
Bring to boil and add rice.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 45 minutes. Uncover.
Stir in corn, tomatoes, chestnuts, green chiles and mustard.
Serve warm.

title: sour cream spice cake
directions: Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 30 to 35 minutes if using 2 round layer pans or 55 minutes in tube pan.
Bake until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Frost with any vanilla frosting or delicious without frosting.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Beat together buttermilk, eggs and baking soda.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, raisins and caraway seed, baking powder and salt.
Stir buttermilk mixture into flour mixture.

title: mission baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese; mix gently.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 475° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake 15 minutes longer.

title: salmon turbot
directions: Pick and remove bones from salmon.
Make a white sauce by mixing butter and flour together and adding one well beaten egg and the milk.
Cook until it thickens, stirring often.
In a baking dish, arrange alternate layers of salmon and white sauce. Cover the top with rolled cracker crumbs; dot with butter and a few tablespoons of milk.
Bake in a hot oven for about 25 minutes.

title: almond broccoli casserole
directions: Trim off leaves of broccoli and remove tough ends of lower stalks.
Wash broccoli thoroughly and cut into spears.
Cook in a small amount of boiling water for 8 minutes.
Drain.

title: refrigerated biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco; add milk and yeast (dissolved in warm water).
Mix well.
Refrigerate until needed. Place biscuits in pan and cook 10 to 15 minutes at 375° (until brown).

title: shortbread
directions: Sift flour and sugar together and blend margarine into mixture.
Add vanilla and blend the mixture together.
Form into small balls and place onto cookie sheet a few inches apart.
With the back of a fork, press the balls down making criss-cross pattern.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool on a wire rack.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat together the sugar, oil and eggs.
Stir in bananas and lemon rind (optional).
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Add to banana mixture.
Stir until combined.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 325°. Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: nora's poor man's cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients with milk.
Beat well.
Pour in large iron skillet and bake at 350° until done.
Very good for strawberry shortcake.

title: strawberry rhubarb pecan salad
directions: In medium saucepan, combine rhubarb, water, sugar and food coloring.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin, stirring to dissolve.
Add cream cheese cubes and stir until melted.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or until mixture begins to thicken. Pour into medium size bowl and fold in whipped cream, strawberries and pecans.
Pour into mold or serving container.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: breakfast egg roll
directions: Beat eggs for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake on a 15 x 10-inch pan for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Slice peaches in dish.
Cut crust off bread. Cut each slice into 3 pieces.
Place on top of peaches. Mix sugar, flour, egg and butter; spoon over bread.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: best beet pickles
directions: Bring water, sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Add beets and boil until beets are hot.
Put in jars and seal.

title: squash casserole
directions: Peel and slice squash.
Put layers of squash and onion, butter, salt and pepper.
Pour spaghetti sauce over squash. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: divinity pie
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Gradually add sugar.
Fold in crackers, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into buttered pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cover when cool with Dream Whip, strawberries and coconut.

title: dill pickles
directions: Select cucumbers about 4 inches long; wash and pack in quart jars.
Add 1/2 of the bloom of dill to each jar.
Boil remaining ingredients; pour over cucumbers while boiling and seal jars. Store.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well and pour all ingredients into pie shell.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and Cool Whip if desired.

title: mushroom pie
directions: Saute mushrooms in chicken fat. Add stock, marjoram, salt and pepper. Cover and let cook 10 minutes.
Thicken with flour.
Add cream and wine. Cover and let simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking. Remove from heat and place in casserole.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° one hour.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Mix all ingredients except cheese together and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peach melba(serves 4)
directions: Drain syrup from fruit into 1-quart casserole.
Stir in jelly and cornstarch.
Microwave at High for 5 to 5 1/2 minutes, or until thickened, stirring 2 times.
Stir fruit into hot sauce. Serve over pound cake if desired.

title: crawfish stew
directions: Heat butter in saucepan; add flour and make medium brown roux. Add onions, bell pepper, garlic, celery and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add crawfish fat, water, seasonings, lemon slice and crawfish.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: mandel bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil, then add the eggs (beaten) and then flour, baking powder, vanilla, nuts and morsels.
Dough will be sticky. Coat hands with flour. Shape into a
log shape and place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until golden brown. Cut into 2-inch slices.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix and blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Cook 30 minutes at 300°, then lower temperature to 250° or 275° and cook another 30 minutes.

title: fish cakes
directions: Mix onion, egg, fish and potatoes together.
Add seasonings. Shape into small cakes.
Coat with flour and fry in butter until brown.

title: pennsylvania dutch style green beans
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove from pan and crumble.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add onion; brown lightly.
Stir in cornstarch, salt and dry mustard.
Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir liquid into skillet and cook, stirring, until mixture starts to boil.
Blend in brown sugar and vinegar.
Add green beans; heat thoroughly.
Turn into serving dish; garnish with egg and crumbled bacon.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Mix flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Add the rest, except eggs, to large mixing bowl.
Mix with wooden spoon, no mixer, until creamy.
Add eggs; add flour mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by walnut size pieces on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: nanny's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and cream cheese.
Add salt and vanilla. Mix well.
Add flour and eggs alternately into batter.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: diet bean mushroom dip
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator overnight.
(Needs to marinate.)
Whirl in blender.
Use as dip or dressing for lettuce and tomato salad.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add milk.
Beat eggs well; add to chocolate mix.
In a bowl, mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Pour and mix well with chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in pie shell. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until tested done with toothpick.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup until you can spin a thread.

title: hot pickled carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut into long strips or spears.
Fill into quart jars along with peppers.
Add salt.
Fill with vinegar and water according to desired
sour taste. Put on tops.
Put jars into large boiler or cold packer.
Cover with salt and heat until boiling begins.
Remove and check for tightness.

title: corn chowder
directions: Put potatoes, celery and onion in a large pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, then reduce heat and simmer for about 20 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender. Drain off water.
Add creamed corn, corn, evaporated milk, cayenne pepper, and salt, and simmer over low heat for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with cornbread or chips.

title: easy sausage quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry (or use pie shell).
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven and gently prick with fork. Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool. Cook sausage until browned; drain. Combine eggs, milk and seasonings in a medium mixing bowl; beat lightly.
Stir in sausage.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup cheese over pastry shell, top with sausage mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Simmer for about 2 hours.
Use as marinade or basting sauce.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: *Usually add about 1/8 to 1/4 cup more, because this dough is quite sticky.

title: far-i-kal(mutton and cabbage)
directions: One of the all time favorites for Sunday dinner.

title: baked parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into quarters (lengthwise).
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a Ziploc bag.
Moisten potatoes with water. Shake a few at a time in the bag, coating potatoes well with cheese mixture.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine in a
13 x 9-inch pan.
Place coated potatoes in a single layer.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour, turning once during baking.

title: quick and easy anchovy dip
directions: Add all ingredients together and stir well.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: lizard tails
directions: Slice cucumbers lengthwise.
Pack in jars with dill (lots). Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat to boil.
Let cool to lukewarm and pour over cukes.
Put in cold pack.
Add cold water to cover jars.
Just bring to boil and remove jars immediately.

title: orange tarragon chicken breasts
directions: Season chicken breasts with salt and garlic powder.
Brown chicken breasts in a little cooking oil in skillet.
Remove from pan and discard oil.

Put back in pan and add orange juice from one orange, about 1/2 cup water, tarragon, bell pepper and celery, orange peel, lemon basil or lemon flavored herb and braise on medium heat until chicken is done, about 30 minutes.
Add cornstarch to 1/4 cup water and blend.
Add this to skillet and thicken sauce.
Serves 4.

title: krispy kole slaw
directions: Shred both cabbages or cut up fine with knife.
Thin slice red onion and green pepper.
Feather carrots with vegetable peeler. Toss all together.
Add vinegar, celery salt and mayonnaise.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: orange roughy almondine
directions: Rinse the fillets and pat dry.
Place in a baking dish to accomodate the number of fillets you are serving.
Drizzle melted margarine over fillets. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds 10 minutes prior to the finished baking time.
Of course, this can be adapted to your microwave.

title: crab meat appetizers
directions: Melt margarine, cheese and drained crab meat in microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Mix.
Spread on quartered English muffins.
Broil for 2 minutes.
Serve. Serves 10 to 15 people.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: I usually double this and add some hot sauce or hot pepper of your choice and amount you like.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Combine apple juice and cornstarch in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Stir in apples.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Cream margarine with sugar; stir in oats, cocoa and vanilla. Shape into balls.
May be rolled in sugar, flaked coconut, roasted almonds or crumbled corn flakes.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Serve over lettuce, cabbage, etc.

title: crocodile brew
directions: Mix nectar, juice, pop and sherbet together.
Serve immediately.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Saute celery, onions and parsley in 3 tablespoons butter. Mix all ingredients, reserving half the bread crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° until bubbly.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Blend spinach, flour, salt and pepper together. Stir in remaining ingredients and put in an 11 x 7-inch casserole dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until set.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, melted butter, vanilla and milk in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Spoon mixture into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Mix softened butter, brown sugar, flour and pecans in a small bowl until crumbly.
Sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Line pie plate with bottom crust.
Pare, core and slice apples and place in pastry-lined plate.
Mix together sugar, flour and cinnamon until it looks like all sugar.
Sprinkle over sliced apples and shake sugar mixture down into the pie.
Dot with butter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place 1/2 croutons in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Heat broth and margarine.
Pour over croutons.
Combine chicken, celery and mayonnaise and spread over top of croutons.
Add chestnuts.
Pour rest of croutons on top.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over all.
Let stand several hours or overnight refrigerated.
When ready to bake, pour mushroom soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add extra mushrooms if desired.

title: chicken-vegetable medley
directions: Spray Pam in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread cooked vegetables on bottom.
Layer cut up chicken on vegetables. Mix the 2 soups with the mayonnaise and soy sauce (and almonds if you use them).
Spread on top of chicken.
Layer cheese on top of sauce.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of asparagus soup

title: date roll
directions: Mix milk and sugar.
Cook until forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add dates.
Cook until almost hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Stir to keep dates from sticking to bottom.
Remove from heat.
Beat until almost cool.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour on a cold cloth that has been rung out of cold water.
Knead into a roll 1 1/2-inches thick.
Slice when it is hard.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix soup,
sour
cream,
milk,	onion, salt and pepper. Add potatoes.
Pour into greased dish.	Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Melt
butter
and	stir in cracker crumbs.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple kuchen (german dessert)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter or margarine into cake mix (dry) until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture slightly into ungreased oblong pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices while warm.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Blend in sour cream and eggs.
Pour over top. Bake for 25 minutes.

title: mexican casserole with beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off fat.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with half of the taco shells.
Season hamburger to your own taste with salt, pepper, garlic salt and chili powder. Sprinkle half the onion over meat.
Pour 1 can of pork and beans over onion.
Place half of cheese over pork and beans.
Make another layer of everything, beginning with shells.
Mix soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Pour soup over top of all.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix well and pour into a well-greased and floured baking pan. Bake at 250° until well done, 40 to
50 minutes.

title: tummy warmer(crock-pot)
directions: Put flour, salt and pepper in cooker.
Add steak strips and stir well. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on high for 1 hour, then on low 8 hours or on high 5 hours.
Serve on rice or noodles.

title: icing for cut out cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add salt, vanilla and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Tint with food coloring, if desired.
Spread on cooled cookies.

title: simply elegant steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
In a large skillet, brown meat in oil using high heat.
Add onions.
Saute until tender-crisp. Blend soup, sherry, liquid from mushrooms and garlic salt.
Pour over steak.
Add mushrooms.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until steak is tender.
Serve over beds of rice.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In top of double boiler (or in boiler on low heat) combine sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk gradually, blending well.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add chocolate when mixture begins to thicken,
stirring constantly until chocolate is blended.
Add small amount of mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Add to mixture in boiler, add vanilla.
Blend well.
Remove from heat when bubbly.
Cool, covered, pour into baked pie crust.
Add meringue.
Brown at 400° for about 10 minutes.
This is good for coconut or pineapple.
Omit chocolate, when mixture is thick add beaten egg yolk and vanilla.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup coconut or 1 small can crushed pineapple, drained.

title: dee's friday special
directions: Place entire mixture in frying pan. Add lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
It does not have to be cooked, just heated. Place generous spoonful on toast rounds.
Top with Russian dressing. May also be served over noodles.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Prepare spaghetti.
In medium bowl combine vegetables and spaghetti.
Add olive oil.
Add dressing.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Stir gently before serving.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Combine ingredients in fondue pot or crock-pot.
Serve with chips.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas and put in mixing bowl.
Add minced onion.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Pour over peas and onion. Stir in chopped eggs.
Chill before serving.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Heat juice and dissolve Jell-O; cool.
Add sherbet and stir until dissolved.
Add fruit and pour into mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Cut margarine into flour; add remaining dry ingredients and orange rind.
Mix well.
Add water to juice to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Mix with egg; fold into dry ingredients.
Add cranberries and nuts.
Bake in greased pans, 60 to 70 minutes, at 350°.

title: squash relish
directions: Combine the squash, onions and salt together.
Let stand overnight.
Then drain.
Add vinegar, sugar, cornstarch, pimentos, peppers, black pepper, nutmeg and turmeric.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
(Do not boil.)
Then seal in jars.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add grated rind.
Mix.
Add 1 cup flour; mix. Add 1/2 cup milk or juice; mix.
Add 1 cup flour; mix.
Add rest of milk or juice.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: oriental stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in wok or skillet.
Add chicken and stir for 2 minutes.
Add vegetables and continue to stir-fry until the vegetables are crisp-tender.
Mix the seasoning, as directed, and pour over mixture.
Stir-fry 1 minute longer.
Serve over rice or chinese noodles.

title: bleu cheese chicken
directions: Melt butter; blend in paprika.
Dredge chicken breasts in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in paprika butter, turning until brown on all sides.
Add onions and consomme.
Cover and cook over low heat 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add sour cream and Bleu cheese.
Continue cooking over low heat 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Line 9-inch pie plate with 1 pie sheet; poke holes all over bottom with fork.
Pour ingredients from bowl into pan; cover and finish with pie crust.
Cut a few decorative slits to vent.
Cook in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes or until crust is golden.

title: la sabe chilli cups
directions: Flatten out biscuits and place in greased muffin tins.
Fill half to three-fourths full with chilli.
Top with squares of cheese.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are brown and cheese is melted.
Makes 20.

title: chocolate pretzels
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening in double boiler over hot water. Stir until smooth.
Using tongs, dip pretzels into chocolate, coating both sides.
Place on wax paper-lined tray.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until set.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts well.
Separate hearts and place in casserole dish.
Cube cheese, mix with mayonnaise and cover the artichoke with the mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until brown.
Serve with crackers.

title: mints
directions: Combine ingredients together in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot boiling water for 2 or 3 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Add 1 cup water to zucchini and boil for 6 minutes.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Boil for 6 more minutes.
Add Jell-O; cook 6 more minutes.
Pour into freezer containers.
Cool and freeze.
Yields 12 (1/2 pints).

title: cheese soup
directions: Using crock-pot or slow cooker, cook all ingredients on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Serve in warm bowls with crisp croutons.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix oleo, confectioners sugar and vanilla well. Sift flour and salt and add to mixture. Add nuts. Chill dough. Roll into small balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 375°. Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: good italian dressing
directions: Mix all together well.
Use a hand rotary (egg) mixer. Refrigerate overnight before serving over your favorite salad.

title: mustard apricot pork chops
directions: Cook preserves and mustard in a small pan over low heat until preserves are melted.
Place pork chops on a lightly greased broiler pan.
Broil about 4 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Brush with half of the apricot mixture.
Turn pork chops and brush with remaining apricot mixture.
Broil 5 minutes more or until juices run clear.
Top with onions.
Serves 4.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Braise meat until lightly brown.
Add onion and brown.
Add sauces and seasonings.
Mix well and cook a little more.
Cut steam off eggplant; wash and slice into 1/4-inch thick slices. Salt and let stand for 1 hour.
Dry the slices and dip in beaten egg and fry in oil until brown.
(Optional:
After dipped in egg, you can dip in flour before frying.)
Arrange in baking dish. Cover with part of meat mixture.
Repeat in layers.
(Optional: Top with grated cheese.)
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until tender.

title: broiled potato wedges
directions: Mix basil, garlic powder and salt into melted butter.
Arrange potatoes on cookie sheet; brush with oil.
Broil 4 inches from heat source for 10 minutes.
Brush with butter mixture.
Broil 5 minutes longer or until lightly browned and tender.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine cheese, flour, butter and salt.
Stir in cereal. Shape into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheets. Flatten slightly with glass dipped in flour.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: hot cinnamon apple cider
directions: Put all ingredients in a pan on the stove and melt the red hot candies.
Once red hots are melted, pour cider into a carafe or crock pot.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. Blend the remaining ingredients, except pie filling. Makes 2 layers; ice cakes and top with pie filling.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Add sugar and beat until blended.
Add oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Fold in chips.
Spread on greased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.
Makes 30 bars.

title: celery casserole
directions: Prepare celery stalks by removing strings.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Add chopped onion and cook until just tender.
Drain. Stir in drained water chestnuts and pimento.
Dilute soup with milk and add to mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Toss cracker crumbs with melted butter. Sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: aunt lela's frosting
directions: Beat on high for 10 to 12 minutes.
Fold in 1/2 cup drained fruit (crushed pineapple or maraschino cherries, chopped), or substitute almond extract for vanilla and add chopped nuts.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in Cheddar cheese.
Stir in onion flakes, dried beef and Worcestershire sauce; blend well. Shape into ball on waxed paper.
Coat well with pecans.
Cover and chill several hours to allow flavors to blend.
Allow to stand at room temperature about 30 minutes before serving with assorted crackers.

title: "dirt"
directions: Crush 1/2 package Oreos.
Layer bottom of container that looks like flowerpot (example: Tupperware lettuce keeper).

title: cranberry whip cream salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save liquid.
Then add enough boiling water to make 1 cup.
Dissolve jello in hot liquid.
Stir in cranberry sauce and nuts.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in grapes, pineapple and Dream Whip.
Put in a buttered 6-cup mold.

title: pavlova
directions: May substitute any favorite combination of fruit (fresh or canned).
Drain fruit well.
Substitute Cool Whip for whipped topping.

title: cocktail franks
directions: In a medium saucepan, mix all ingredients.
Bring to a slow boil.
Add sliced, cooked hot dog pieces and reduce heat to low. Simmer about 5 minutes.

title: amy lynn's favorite funnel cakes
directions: Beat together milk and eggs.
Beat in flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Pour liquid in pan with oil in it.
Cook at 375°.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased pie plate 30-35 minutes at 325°.
Do not preheat oven.

title: beef and rice stroganoff in a skillet
directions: Brown beef in a 12-inch skillet.
Drain.
Stir in water, rice, salt, garlic, onion, soup and catsup.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook over low heat about 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper, salt and 1/2 of the French fried onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole sprayed with Pam. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Top with remaining onions, return to stove and cook until onions are golden brown.

title: meat pie roma
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add green pepper and cook until tender. Stir in sauce mix, water and tomato paste.
Simmer 10 minutes. Line greased 9-inch pie plate with biscuits.
Press together to seal bottom and along sides of pan.

title: strawberry refrigerator cake
directions: Slowly add lemon juice to sweetened condensed milk; stir until thick.
Add sliced strawberries and beaten egg whites.
Line bottom of 1-quart glass dish with vanilla wafers.
Cover with strawberry mixture.
Alternate with wafers and strawberry mixture until mixture is used.
Put a layer of wafers on top.
Chill for 6 hours or longer.
Serves 8.

title: cookie pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spread crust in a pie plate or in a sheet
cake
pan
and
bake
about
15 minutes at 350°. Crust in pie plate may take less time.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet with a little of the sauce.
Place in baking dish with remaining sauce, oranges and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: twinkies
directions: Line baking pan with split Twinkies.
Dissolve orange jello and let stand until partially set.
Whip it and fold in pineapple. Fold in ice cream.
Pour over Twinkies and chill until set. Cut into squares and serve.

title: duke's apple pizza
directions: Mix 1 1/4 cups flour and 1 teaspoon salt; cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add cheese.
Sprinkle water over mixture; mix and shape into a ball.
Roll pastry dough into 15-inch circle on floured surface.
Place on pizza pan, turning up edges.

title: chi chi cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cake mix, egg and water for 2 minutes on medium speed; add coconut.
Pour into baking pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven when done.
While hot, poke holes in cake and pour cream of coconut over top with crushed pineapple.
Let cool.
Ice with 2 cups of whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top and refrigerate.

title: goulash more
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add onion, bell pepper and meat; saute until tender. Add tomato sauce, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper. Simmer 20 minutes.
Combine with macaroni and corn.
Place mixture in 2-quart casserole or Pyrex pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese during last 10 minutes of baking.

title: potato topped frankfurters
directions: Prepare instant mashed potatoes as directed on package. Add onion,
parsley flakes and dry mustard.
Slit frankfurters lengthwise and stuff with mashed potato mixture.
Top with 1/4 cup of	shredded
cheese and sprinkle top with paprika.
Place in 12 x 7 1/2 x
2-inch
baking
dish
and	microwave
to 4 minutes, turning dish
halfway
through cooking.
Depending on microwave, you may have to cook longer until hot.

title: baked beans for 100 people
directions: Check beans for small rocks and wash them.
Soak beans overnight.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel and slice 2 pounds of carrots.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Layer carrots, green bell pepper (cut in strips) and onion (sliced thin).
Mix tomato soup, black pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Pour over carrots, peppers and onions.
Let set overnight.

title: tennessee treats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, mix brown sugar and eggs.
Add honey and stir.
Add baking powder to water and mix.
Add water to mixing bowl.
Combine flour and spices and stir into mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and stir. Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
To determine when treats are ready, insert toothpick.
A nearly dry toothpick indicates they are done.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: pear relish
directions: Cook syrup 5 minutes then add ground mixture.
Simmer together for 5 minutes.
Pour into hot jars, and seal.

title: lazy daisy salad
directions: Dump all ingredients together, juice and all.
Stir.
Add extra mandarin oranges, if you like; be sure to drain these.

title: debby lewis barbecue sauce and ribs
directions: Mix and cook 15 to 20 minutes. Boil ribs until tender. Remove from water. Pour sauce over ribs and marinate at least 6 hours or up to 24 hours in refrigerator. Put on grill and heat ribs until hot.

title: grandma's fresh coconut candy
directions: Drain milk from coconut and add water to make 1 cup.
Open coconut, peel brown skin from outside and run through fine meat grinder.
To 2 cups sugar, add the liquid, stir until sugar dissolves.
Then cook over moderate heat for 5 minutes.
Add the ground coconut and cream of tartar and boil 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool, then beat until it thickens.
Pour into buttered pan and let it reset.
Slice and stand back.

title: spinach and cracked wheat
directions: Wash spinach.
Brown onions in oil.
Add spinach on top of onions and let steam.
Add washed cracked wheat on top of spinach. Cover tightly and steam about 10 mins.
Stir together.
Cover for another 10 mins.
Add a little water if necessary.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter or oleo, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time and peanut butter. Add the flour, soda, pinch of salt and vanilla.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Good to place Hershey's Kiss in center on removal from oven.

title: baked seafood casserole
directions: Combine crabmeat and shrimp with vegetables which have been chopped fine.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper and add Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Cover with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt, pepper and paprika.
Put oil in skillet.
Heat and brown chops.
Drain off any excess oil.
Add 1 cup of water, celery and onion soup mix.
Cover and cook on low heat for 40 minutes or until chops are tender.
Remove chops from pan.
Combine flour, parsley and 1/4 cup water.
Blend in pan juices.
Add milk and mushrooms.
Cook over low heat until thick and bubbly.
Return chops to sauce.
Let stand for a few minutes. Serves 6. Serve with mashed potatoes and spoon extra sauce over potatoes.

title: chinese carrots
directions: Shred carrots coarsely. Melt butter in skillet and add carrots. Sprinkle with salt and sugar. Cover and cook for 8 to 10 minutes. Top with parsley. Serves 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and butter.
Add vanilla.
Slightly beat eggs and add to mixture.
Mix together the flour, salt and baking soda and add to mixture.
Add oats, raisins and sunflower seeds.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: grandma's soup bean dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients, then drop by tablespoon onto top of soup beans (that are done), about 20 minutes before eating time. Cover and cook on low heat for 20 minutes, turning over once.

title: blueberry spread(diabetic)
directions: Combine blueberries, 1/2 cup water and lemon juice in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil; simmer gently for about 8 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: curried chicken
directions: Wash the chicken and rub with the garlic.
Place on foil covered cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until very light brown.
Brush with the honey, butter and curry powder melted together.
Bake until brown. Cover with the chicken soup.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: grape hull pies(makes 2)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in pot and cook on low heat until margarine melts. Then pour into partly baked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool (optional).
Top with meringue and bake.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Freezes well.
Very good during holiday season.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat with fork.
Add coconut and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Gradually add the water, stirring with a fork (dough will be crumbly).
Turn onto a floured surface and knead into a soft ball.
Divide the dough in half and let stand 10 minutes.
Roll each half into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle and cut into 2 1/2-inch squares. (Do not re-roll or patch dough.)
Deep fry a few at a time in fat until golden brown. Drain on paper towels and serve with Honey Butter or roll in cinnamon and sugar.

title: chicken with creamy noodles
directions: Shake chicken in seasoned flour in a bag and reserve flour. Brown chicken pieces in oil and drain on paper towels.
Lightly saute onion and garlic.
Return chicken to pan and add water, lemon juice and bouillon cube.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Stir 2 tablespoons seasoned flour into juices left in pan and gradually blend in sour cream.
Return to medium heat to warm sour cream mixture but do not allow it to boil.
Add cooked, hot noodles and toss to coat.
Serve immediately with chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add butter, which has been melted in the pan you cook the pudding in.
Add rice and milk. Mix well and add raisins and nutmeg.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Cook at 350° for one hour or until thickened.

title: shortcake("want-ta-be")
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan spread vanilla wafer cookies.
Crush and spread strawberries.
Slice kiwis and cover strawberries.
Add thick layer of whipped cream (from scratch) and top with sliced bananas.
One slice is enough.
Enjoy!

title: strawberry meringue pie
directions: Thaw berries.
Berries must be crushed.
Combine cornstarch and sugar.
Mix with berries.
Cook over low heat until clear and thick.
When cool, pour into shell.
Just before serving, cover with whipping cream.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt butter and add seasonings.
Mix cereal, nuts, etc.
Pour butter mixture in shallow pan and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir up once.
Store in covered container when cool.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for two minutes and pour into a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: saturday night special
directions: Brown meat in 1 tablespoon fat.
Add onion.
Cook until brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Serve on toasted bun.

title: creamy potato puff
directions: Mix potatoes, cream cheese, egg and salt together until creamy.
Add onion and pimento.
Put in ungreased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Double for company.
Can be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: arkansas traveler oven round steak
directions: Line baking pan with foil.
Dot 1/2 stick of margarine on bottom.
Sprinkle 1/2 onion soup.
Lay steak pieces on margarine. Dot remaining margarine on top of steak; sprinkle with remaining soup.
Cover with green beans.
Do not drain.
Add potatoes.
Add foil to top and fold closed with the bottom of foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cheese spread for rye
directions: Mix together and spread on cocktail rye bread, the small loaves.
Broil until bubbly.

title: veggie salad
directions: Brown bacon and crumble in a bowl.
Toss all ingredients together and serve with creamy cucumber dressing (or your favorite).

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Save some cherries for top.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease muffin tins.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Crush 1/2 cup berries; add to batter.
Fold in remaining berries.
Spoon into muffin tin; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°. Makes 12 to 24 muffins, depending on pans.

title: breakfast applesauce bars
directions: Mix flour, oats, baking soda and cinnamon in medium-size bowl and set aside.
Mix applesauce, honey and vanilla in small bowl and add to above.
Stir until combined.
Add dried fruit, raisins and walnuts.
Spray a 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Spread mixture evenly in the prepared pan and bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool in dish on wire rack; cut into bars.
Store in tightly covered container or in freezer.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Heat water to boiling; peel and dice potatoes.
Drop into boiling water to shock potatoes.
Cook until potatoes can be easily broken apart with a fork.
Drain off water.
Place kettle of potatoes back on ther burner and stir to remove all remaining moisture.
Be careful not to scorch.
Remove from heat.
Whip with mixer, adding butter and milk to desired consistency.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut up and skin chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Dip chicken in buttermilk.
Shake in a plastic bag, in which you have combined wheat germ, potato flakes, garlic salt and paprika.
Place chicken on a baking dish, that has been sprayed with nonstick oil.
Bake in oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients except pepper.
Put in 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover for the last 5 minutes to let brown.
Sprinkle with ground pepper.
Serve hot with chips or sliced bread squares.

title: ham sauce
directions: Mix sugar and mustard.
Add eggs and vinegar.
Cook until thickened in double boiler.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Mix well and place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, top with crushed potato chips and bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until bubbly and brown.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy crispy chicken
directions: Roll chicken pieces in mayonnaise and then in cracker or Rice Krispies crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: party ham sandwiches
directions: Heat mustard, Worcestershire sauce, margarine and poppy seed enough to melt margarine and dissolve mustard.

title: crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Mix together 1 can of cream of chicken soup with first 6 ingredients, to make dressing.
Then put 1/2 of other can of soup in bottom of crock-pot.
Then layer 1/2 of dressing mixture, next put 1/2 of cooked chicken, then other half of dressing and rest of chicken, cover the top with rest of chicken soup.
Cook on low for 3 hours.

title: fudge meltaways
directions: Mix together all but frosting.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: nani's pink stuff
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 pint hot water.
Add marshmallows and cream cheese; stir until melted.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple.
Pour into oblong casserole.
Chill until slightly set. Add whipping cream and nuts; let set until firm.

title: chili tortilla chips
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Lightly spray tortillas with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle with chili powder. Turn tortillas over and repeat process. Stack 2 to 3 tortillas and cut into 8 wedges; repeat process. Place on cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until crisp and lightly browned. Makes 12 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix well butter, soup, cheese, sour cream, salt and onion. Combine with hash browns (thawed).
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed cornflakes and drizzle one stick of melted butter over all.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Drain all fruits.
Arrange fruits in layers in order given in well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter. Add flour, sugar, curry and sherry to melted butter and stir until thick.
Pour this sauce over fruit.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Lightly brown beef in heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Add onion and cook until tender, but not browned.
Add corn, soups, sour cream, pimento, salt and pepper.
Stir in cooked drained noodles. Spoon into a 4-quart casserole dish.
Combine Ritz crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat together the eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Place dry bread crumbs in an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle raisins over bread.
Pour egg mixture over all. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: holiday snack
directions: Put crackers in large roaster, combine rest of the ingredients and pour over crackers, stir to coat each piece.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: mint chocolate chip pie
directions: Spoon ice cream into crust. In a microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate; stir until smooth. Drizzle over ice cream. Freeze for 6 to 8 hours or overnight. Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato biscuits
directions: Put in a mixing bowl first 2 ingredients.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Beat thoroughly.
Cover; let rise until light.
Add 2 cups flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and again let rise to about double in size.
Turn onto a floured board.
Pat and roll 1/4-inch thick.
Shape in any shape desired.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 20 minutes according to size of the biscuits.
Makes about 18.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butterscotch chips and margarine in medium saucepan.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press half the mixture firmly onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Put hamburger and onion in iron skillet, no shortening, until slightly brown.
Add sugar, chili powder, salt, pepper and sugar. Add ketchup and let simmer until thick, being sure to keep it from sticking.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, onion, pineapple and pepper and form into ball. (Should be moist.)
Roll in crushed nuts.
Top with cherry. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: jiffy orange nut bread
directions: Grease loaf pan or cake pan.
Blend flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.
Melt butter in boiling water.
Blend in orange rind, orange juice, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Add dry ingredients; add nuts.
Stir just until all is blended well. Batter will be lumpy.
Pour in pan.
Put walnut halves on top of batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pumpkin crunch or pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and cinnamon in large bowl. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin. Top with pecans. Drizzle butter over pecans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown. Cool. Serve with whipped topping.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix together the sugar, butter and 2 egg yolks, beating well. Add to this mixture the juice and rind of 1 lemon.
Then add the flour, milk and the 2 egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Pour in a cooked pie crust and bake 45 minutes in slow oven at 300°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: (Use 9 x 13 dish.)
Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Place chicken on top.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover for last 15 minutes.

title: gingerbread(heart healthy)
directions: Using low speed of electric mixer, blend molasses, brown sugar, oil and spices.
Add boiling water.
Blend.
Gradually add flour.
Beat 2 minutes until smooth. Dissolve baking soda in 2 tablespoons hot water. Add to batter.
Blend.
Pour into an 8-inch sprayed or Teflon lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with whipped cream substitute.

title: see's marshmallow fudge
directions: Cook first three ingredients to boiling point and then boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add the butter, chocolate bits, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Mix until all is dissolved and pour into 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine mayonnaise, 3/4 cup cheese, Old Bay seasoning, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Fold in crab meat.
Spoon mixture into 1-quart casserole; top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with a dash of Old Bay seasoning.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until mixture begins to bubble around edges.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add onion to rest of the ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake it at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm and brown slightly.

title: wild card chili
directions: Brown beef with onion in a Dutch oven.
Pour over fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.
Simply wild.

title: broccoli and cheese hot dish
directions: Mix together.
Bake 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Combine dry with undrained fruit, mixing well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 7 1/2 x 11 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts, if desired.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.
Do not attempt to mold as mixture will not be firm. Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: little meat loaves
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients with 1 can tomato sauce. Form mixture into 6 loaves.
Place in shallow baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Skim off excess fat.
Combine remaining tomato sauce with gravy mix and water.
Pour over loaves. Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to directions; drain and pour into casserole dish.
Stir in cheese and 1/2 stick margarine.
Heat the other 1/2 stick margarine.
Stir into Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle crackers over broccoli and bake for 25 minutes.

title: crockpot macaroni & cheese
directions: Spray crockpot with vegetable spray.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into crockpot and cook on high 3 hours.
Add 1/2 cup grated cheese 30 minutes before end of cooking time.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cookie crumbs, sugar and melted margarine.
Pat into a pie pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir in large bowl the sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, soda, zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Beat eggs and oil in separate bowl.
Pour over flour mixture and stir until moistened. Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for one hour and thirty minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Turn out on cooling rack.
Turn top side up and cool completely.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients.
Drain. Add rice (can be Minute rice), lemon juice, salad dressing, curry powder, crushed pineapple, grated onion, coconut and chopped celery. Chill.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Cut sausage in bite size pieces.
Saute in pan for about 10 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Put sausage, sliced peppers and sliced onion in roasting pan.
Add oil, salt, pepper, onion and tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Bake at 350° until peppers are soft (about 45 minutes).

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots, until tender, but firm.
Mix other ingredients well.
Add drained carrots carefully and let set for at least 1 day.

title: tuna noodle bake
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and celery in butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and brown.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: apple tapioca pudding
directions: Combine water and lemon juice.
Pour over apples in greased shallow baking dish.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes or until apples are partly cooked.
Mix together tapioca, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over apples, mixing thoroughly.
Add butter.
Continue baking 10 minutes.
Stir well and bake 5 minutes longer.
Serve hot or cold with cream (optional).

title: crab meat hors d'oeuvres
directions: Whip last 4 ingredients in food processor.
Add crab meat and mix.
Toast and cool English muffins.
Cut each muffin into quarters.
Spread mix on muffin pieces.
Freeze pieces on a cookie sheet for at least 30 minutes.
Store in plastic freezer bag. Before serving, heat on cookie sheet in a 350° oven (approximately 20 minutes).

title: french toast
directions: Beat egg and add to milk; mix well.
Add spices.
Dip each side of each slice of regular bread in milk mixture to coat each side.
Brown each side in melted margarine on hot flat grill pan. Serve with pancake syrup.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together and chill until set.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan.
Spread cherry pie filling in pan. Blend sugar, flour, oats, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter together until crumbly.
Spread over cherries.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana cream pie(heritage recipe)
directions: Mix cream cheese with 1/4 c. milk.
Cook pudding with rest of milk until thick.
Mix with cream cheese.
Slice bananas into bottom of graham cracker crust, then pour in filling.
Sprinkle coconut over pie. Do not bake.
Let chill for at least an hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain and cool.
Chop pepper, onions, seeded tomatoes and celery into small pieces.
Add vegetables to spaghetti; mix.
Add Salad Supreme seasoned salt and Zesty Italian dressing (do not substitute).
Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: glazed fresh apple cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet and cook 11 to 14 minutes at 400°.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: salmon salad with fresh dill
directions: Flake salmon.
Mix all ingredients.
Can be used as a salad or as a sandwich spread.

title: ho-ho beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon and set aside.
Brown ground beef and onion in bacon grease.
Drain meat; crumble bacon and mix with ground beef.
Mix remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco pie
directions: Line bottom and sides of pie tin with crescent rolls.
Crush chips and put on rolls.
Brown hamburger and strain.
Mix hamburger, sour cream, water and taco seasoning.
Put on chips. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter.
Add vanilla.
Take away from heat and slowly add sugar.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Smash sweet potato, then mix with remaining ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350°.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Put in large pot and bring to boil, stirring constantly. After it starts to boil, cook 10 minutes more, no longer, stirring constantly.
Take off stove and add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Mix.
Pour in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Makes 4 1/2 pounds.

title: tropical fruit cake
directions: Blend cake mix, eggs and fruit.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top of batter with coconut. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
No need to frost.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms, remove stems and finely chop.
Melt margarine in frypan.
Add onions, pepperoni, green pepper, garlic and stems. Cook until tender but not brown.
Add crackers, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in broth.
Stuff caps, rounding tops.
Cook in shallow baking pan in 1/4-inch broth. Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: orange-sugared pecans
directions: Mix sugar and water in heavy pan.
Cook without stirring to soft ball stage; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in orange rind, orange juice and salt.
Add pecans; stir until sugar begins to crystallize.
Turn out onto cold baking sheets. Separate nuts, using two forks.
Let harden.

title: kid pleasing cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Add egg, milk and margarine. Beat with eggbeater until nearly smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Bake in 8-inch square greased pan in 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together in order.
Bake for 45 minutes or until the center springs back when lightly touched.
