Ice with German chocolate icing.

title: boiled frosting
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients slowly until hard-ball stage. Add the egg whites and vanilla.

title: cream puffs
directions: Add butter to boiling water.
Melt, add flour and salt at once.
Cook, stirring until smooth and forms a soft ball.
Cool mixture and add eggs, one at a time.
Drop batter onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes and then at 325° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 Cream Puffs. Cool, then cut and fill with any cream or pudding.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Put butter and brown sugar in cast-iron skillet.
Melt brown sugar and butter.
Then put fruit and nuts on top of sugar and butter.
Put eggs, white sugar, juice, flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pour on top of fruit and nuts.
Bake in cast-iron skillet at 350 degrees until done.

title: nachos
directions: In large skillet, lightly brown meat; drain.
Add bell pepper and onion strips.
Add taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer on low until onions and bell pepper are tender.
Line bottom of large serving pan with chips.
Top with meat mixture.
Add cheese on top with taco sauce and sour cream.

title: oat raisin loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Pour water over oats in large bowl; stir until moistened. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in casserole dish at 350° until hot throughout.

title: z.o.t.ch.(zucchini, onions, tomatoes and cheese)
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan.
Saute zucchini and onions, a little at a time, until transparent or just beginning to brown. Transfer to ovenproof casserole dish.
Season with salt, pepper and basil as you saute.
When all zucchini is cooked, add tomato to zucchini.
Cover and cook at 325° for 45 minutes or microwave for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Drain liquid with turkey baster. (Save it to add to vegetable soup!)
Top with cheese. Return to oven for 5 minutes (no cover), or microwave for 5 minutes, covered.

title: molded ambrosia
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Keep 1/3 cup for the top.
Press remaining crumb mixture into a baking dish.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Dissolve jello and sugar in the water.
Stir in the pineapple syrup and chill until partly set.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Whip until fluffy.
Fold in pineapple, oranges and coconut.
Pour over crumbs in dish and sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Chill until firm and cut into squares.
Top with cherries.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter together. Fold in cool whip and put in crust. Refrigerate.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake by directions on box. Cool and split layers with long thin knife. Mix sour cream, confectioners sugar and flavorings in deep bowl. Add coconut, all except 1/2 cup. Chill 1 hour in freezer. Spread icing between all layers and top of cake. Sprinkle coconut on top of cake and chill. Keep refrigerated until all gone.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter.
Add other ingredients and add mushrooms.
Saute 5 minutes.
Delicious served with steak or roast.

title: mom's cooked cabbage slaw dressing
directions: Combine.
Blend well and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Cool and spread over shredded cabbage.

title: beets and pineapple
directions: Cook saved juices in small saucepan with cornstarch, sugar and vinegar.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens.
Add salt, pepper, beets, pineapple and butter.
Cook for 20 minutes.
May be served hot or cold.

title: chocolate chip pudding pan cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixing bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; then stir in chips (batter will be stiff).
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: old time gingerbread
directions: Sift into a large bowl the flour, salt, soda, ginger and cinnamon.
Cream butter light and fluffy.
Add sugar to butter, beating well.
Add eggs and milk to cream mixture.
Stir in molasses.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until done.

title: instant easter pie
directions: If desired, reserve a few chunks of pineapple and some Cool Whip for garnish.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat well at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each addition.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with sour cream; begin and end with flour.
Mix until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
If desired, garnish with grated lemon peel after sprinkling with powdered sugar.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: In 9-inch quiche dish or deep pie plate, spread beans in bottom.
Spread avocado on top of beans.
Sprinkle diced tomatoes on avocado.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise together and spread mix over tomatoes.
Sprinkle taco seasoning on sour cream mix (more or less to taste).
Cover with white cheese, then less of the orange cheese.
Arrange scallions and black olives on top.
Serve with white tortilla chips and salsa.

title: brown sugar icing
directions: Bring this to a boil and add 3/4 box of 4x sugar.
Boil only long enough to melt butter; it needs to be thin.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cover the bottom of an 8 x 12 1/2-inch casserole with broccoli, chestnuts and cauliflower.
Lay slices of cheese over to cover.
Add celery or mushroom soup and spread over cheese good.
Place over all, the Stove Top dressing.
When ready to bake, sprinkle water over crumbs until lightly damp or moist. Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cook vegetables until lightly tender before making casserole.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and flour.
Slowly add to sugar mixture. Hand mix in zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour 1 large or 2 small loaf pans.
Pour in pan(s).
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix 2 puddings and jello in saucepan.
Add water or use juice from oranges; mix and bring to a boil.
Pour into dish and add drained oranges.
Refrigerate to set.

title: stir-fried snow peas(healthful eating)
directions: In a nonstick skillet, heat olive oil, garlic, ginger and red pepper.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add snow peas.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or just until crisp-tender.

title: orange ice cream salad
directions: Use pineapple juice for some liquid.

title: hearty winter soup
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Coat chicken with combined flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and water; coat with combined crumbs and cheese.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon together.
Put bacon on top. Bake at 300° until bacon is cooked.

title: florida key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly; blend with condensed milk, 1/4 cup sugar, lime juice and cornstarch in top of double boiler.
Cook until slightly thickened; turn into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until very stiff.
Pile on top of pie, being sure to cover entire crust. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until brown.
Cool on rack away from drafts.
Chill.

title: 7 layer taco dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning with beans and spread in deep bowl.
Spread avocado dip on top of beans, then spread sour cream.
Place black olives or chiles on top of sour cream. Spread grated cheese; add tomatoes and top with green onion. Serve cold with tortilla chips.

title: tomato-beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles. Add butter, and stir to coat the noodles. Add cream cheese, sour cream and chopped green onions. Mix well. Brown the beef with garlic. Add sauce, salt, sugar, and pepper. Simmer 20 minutes covered. Alternate layers of beef mix and noodle mix in a greased casserole dish. Top with cheddar cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees. Recipe may be easily doubled.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients; pour into greased spring pan. Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Leave in oven 3 to 4 hours (after oven is shut off).

title: pretzel salad or dessert
directions: Cream together the butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix in the pretzels and press into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 6 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together the cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Spread over pretzel layer and refrigerate 40 minutes.
Combine the strawberry gelatin and boiling water, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in the strawberries.
Pour over the cream cheese layer.
Chill until set. Makes 10 servings.

title: ratatouille
directions: Layer vegetables, sprinkling seasonings on each layer.
Press vegetables down tightly.
Cook on top of stove over low heat about 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange fluff cake
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks until lemon colored.
Add rind and orange and salt.
Add flour and 1/2 cup of the sugar, sifted together 3 times.
Beat egg whites until frosty.
Add cream of tartar and remaining salt and sugar and beat until it looks like frosting.
Then fold the yellow part into the white and put in angel food pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Invert after taking out of oven until cool.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Chill overnight.
Serve with cut up vegetables.

title: sugar cookies or "tea cakes"
directions: Cream butter or margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs together. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix all ingredients together.
Blend well.
Refrigerate for 10 to 15 minutes or until hard.
Roll out, then cut with cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for about 12 minutes.
Try baking at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Do not use electric mixer!
Mix oil and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Add flour.
Add apples, coconut and nuts.
Put batter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with bits and bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: fiesta cheese dip
directions: Place all ingredients in crock pot. Cook on low for approximately 2 hours or until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally. Serve from crockpot with chips on side.

title: fried corn
directions: Clean corn and cut from cob.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Start bacon in skillet, then add potatoes.
When bacon is about crisp and potatoes are getting soft, add remaining ingredients and fry over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes, stirring often.

title: fig and almond pinwheels
directions: Combine figs, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat. Cook uncovered 10 minutes until thick.
Remove.
Stir in almonds. Cool.
Stir together flour, salt and baking soda in large bowl to mix well.
Set aside.

title: perfect punch
directions: Chill punch bowl for 1 hour in freezer before mixing.
Combine both juices in punch bowl.
Stir well.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls and stir.
Ready to serve.
Delicious!

title: red, white and blue cobbler
directions: Place blueberry pie filling in bottom of 8 x 8-inch glass baking pan.
Spread evenly and then place the cherry pie filling on top, smoothing to edges of pan.
Place in 400° oven to heat while preparing topping.

title: divinity
directions: Dissolve sugar, syrup and salt over low heat, stirring.
Cook, without stirring, to 248° or to firm ball stage (or light crack stage, 265°).
Wash down with a damp cloth any crystals that may form on the sides of the pan during cooking.
Remove from heat and pour gradually over the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add extract and continue beating until mixture will hold its shape when dropped by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Can use sugar free pudding and lite topping.

title: bread filling
directions: In food processor or blender, place soup, milk, butter or margarine, onion, celery, salt, pepper and parsley.
Blend or chop until vegetables are finely chopped and mixture is well blended. Pour over bread and mix well.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: While toasting bread, mix sugar and cinnamon.
Then spread butter on toast.
Sprinkle mixture on top.
Serve at once.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes and cook in water and salt.
Cook until tender. Drain off water, reserving the liquid.
Add onion soup mix and butter to potatoes.
Add potato water and milk; heat and serve.

title: pimento and cheese
directions: Melt cheese with milk in double boiler.
Mix pimento, eggs, vinegar and sugar together.
Add to cheese mixture.
Cook about 25 minutes on low heat.
Cool and add mayonnaise.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar in a pie pan.
Make a well in the center.
Add oil and milk.
Mix quickly with fork.
Press into pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.
Very flaky and light.
Pie crust may be filled with any cream filling or may be used for lemon meringue pie.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: key lime snow
directions: In a large bowl, sprinkle unflavored gelatin over cold water; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar until blended.
Add boiling water; stir until gelatin is completely dissolved (about 3 minutes).
Add lime peel and juice.
Chill until slightly thickened (about 15 minutes).
In a medium bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
While beating gradually add gelatin mixture; beat until soft peaks form.
Spoon into 8 dessert cups.
Chill until firm (about 2 hours).

title: nothing cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Sift flour and soda together. Alternately add flour and pineapple to creamed mixture. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash and soft margarine with potato masher.
Add egg (beaten), saltines and sweet milk.
Salt to taste.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch dish and top with a few more crushed saltines and margarine.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until slightly brown on top.

title: lemon sherbet
directions: In a small bowl, beat egg whites until they hold soft peaks. Gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar until they hold stiff peaks. Without washing beater, in medium or large bowl, beat egg yolks and remaining 1/4 cup sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in lemon juice until blended.

title: barbecue sauce for pork or beef
directions: Heat ingredients in saucepan, stirring until all ingredients are dissolved.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box for a sheet cake. When cake is cooled in pan, take a fork and make holes over top cake. Mix the condensed milk and cream of coconut together. Pour over cake. Let mixture soak into cake and top
with coconut.

title: lasy day lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, mix eggs with cottage cheese, mozzarella cheese and spices until well blended; set aside.
In another bowl, mix together spaghetti sauce and cooked ground beef.
In a 12 x 8 x 2 inch baking dish, spread 3/4 cup of the meat sauce.
Layer 3 uncooked noodles on top of the meat sauce.
Spread with half of the cottage cheese mixture and 1 1/2 cups of meat sauce.
Layer 3 more uncooked noodles on top of meat sauce.
Spread with remaining cottage cheese mixture.
Top with remaining 3 uncooked noodles and remaining meat sauce.
Pour water around edges of casserole. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more, or until noodles are tender.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with grated parmesan cheese. Makes 6 servings.

title: mushroom potatoes
directions: Mix soup and milk; heat slowly.
Add salt, pepper and onion. Arrange a layer of potatoes in a greased casserole.
Pour on 1/2 of mushroom soup and repeat layers.
Dot with butter and paprika on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Add molasses.
Then combine liquid and dry ingredients alternately.
Let rise, covered, for 15 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine soup, milk and pepper; set aside.
Arrange potatoes, onion, cheese and soup in layers in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more, or until potatoes are tender.

title: sugarless fruit cookies
directions: Sift flour and soda; set aside.
Boil raisins, dates and apples for 3 minutes in 1 cup of water.
Remove from heat; add margarine.
Stir until melted.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients, adding nuts last.
Mix by hand.
Chill.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes.
Yields 40 to 50 small cookies.

title: pork chops casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Arrange in dish.
Sprinkle with onion.
Add rice.
Bring cream of chicken soup and 1 can of water to a boil; pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: venison stew
directions: Brown meat with garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Add rest of ingredients, except large veggies.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add potatoes, carrots with flour, and water.
Cook until thick.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak in butter, add chopped or sliced onion.
Add 2 cans of beef broth to cover meat; simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: super creamy cocoa
directions: In 3-quart saucepan combine cocoa and salt.
Add sweetened condensed milk; mix well.
Over medium heat, slowly stir in water; heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Serve with marshmallows. Refrigerate any leftovers.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: sneaky pete
directions: Mix in a large container with lid.
Mix cranberry juice and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add remaining ingredients; stir and put in freezer until snow cone or slush like, 2 or 3 days.
Stir and serve.

title: cola chicken(microwave)
directions: Place chicken in a ceramic container.
Pour cola over poultry. Cook, covered, on High for 15 minutes.
Rearrange pieces and turn over after 7 minutes.
Drain off 1/4 cup of cola.
Sprinkle chicken with salt.
Cover with catsup.
Cook at High or Full power 10 minutes. Eat and enjoy.

title: grilled hershey sandwich
directions: Heat skillet.
Butter one side of each slice of bread.
Put butter side down of one slice of bread in skillet.
Place Hershey bar on top of this.
Place other slice of bread on top of Hershey bar, with butter side up.
When bottom slice of bread is browned, turn sandwich over and brown other side.

title: turtle cake
directions: Unwrap caramels and put in top of double boiler with evaporated milk.
Heat to dissolve caramels.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using oleo in place of oil. Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Do not use spray oil.)
Put 1/2 of cake mixture in pan and bake at 350° until bubbly and puffy, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Put the caramel and milk mixture on top of first cake layer, then nuts and chocolate chips.
Cover with balance of cake mixture and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
If desired, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and stir ground beef in 10-inch skillet until brown. Stir in macaroni sauce mix, water, chili powder and cayenne pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook for 5 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes.
Place lettuce, green pepper, tomatoes and onions in large bowl; toss with ground beef mixture.
Serve immediately or if desired, cover and refrigerate until chilled, at least 4 hours.
Serve with dairy sour cream if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Can use chips also.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix it with crumbs; press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla together until creamy.
Spread mixture onto crust.
Slice bananas; put on, then add pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on.
Swirl chocolate syrup on top.
Put cherries and nuts on.

title: rocky road cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except frosting.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool, then frost.

title: chewy cake
directions: Put sugar in a bowl and break eggs into sugar.
Mix real well. Stir in flour.
Then stir in pecans.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: coffee punch
directions: Mix ingredients together until sugar is dissolved, then chill. To serve, pour coffee mixture over 1 quart vanilla ice cream in a large punch bowl.
Top with 1 cup heavy cream, whipped.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
Serves 15 to 18.

title: stuffed mushrooms italiano(microwave)
directions: Wash mushrooms; gently remove stems and finely chop.
Drain caps on paper toweling.
In 1-quart bowl combine butter, chopped stems, 1 onion, pepperoni, green pepper and garlic.
Cook at High for 2 minutes, until tender.
Stir in crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper; mix well.
Mound mixture in the mushroom caps.
Place caps in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and cook at Medium or cook power 5 (50%) for 4 minutes, until hot.
Makes 12 appetizers.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Layer in 9 x 12-inch dish in order listed:
tortillas, boned chicken (cut in pieces) and chopped onions.
Mix and heat in saucepan mushroom soup, chicken soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle garlic salt over mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate ribbon coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 cup of the coconut evenly in shallow pan.
Toast 7 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Cool.

title: a mexican dish
directions: Saute onion, garlic, pepper and sausage (out of casing and broken up) until brown.
Add black beans.
Grease a 9 x 13 1/2-inch casserole.
Take each tortilla; add a large spoonful of mixture. Roll up and place one next to another until all ingredients are used up.
Sprinkle cheese (grated) over tortillas, then place 2 cups salsa over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Peel and seed cucumber.
Chop very fine.
Add other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Let set overnight.
Serve with large corn chips.

title: no fail divinity(microwave)
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water and salt in a 2-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave 19 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Candy thermometer should read 260°.
If not, cook 1 or 2 minutes more. Beat egg whites while syrup cooks, very stiff in large mixing bowl.
Add syrup.
Beat 12 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts in; drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook rice and broccoli.
Saute onions and celery in oleo.
Mix Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup and almonds into onions and celery.
Mix all together; pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Break eggs into dry mixture; beat vigorously until mixed well.
Add melted butter, lemon juice and milk; mix well.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake in preheated oven (450°) for 10 minutes, then lower heat to 350° and finish baking until done.

title: cereal sweets
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to a boil.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well and add salt.
Add dry cereal.
Mix well all together.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
You may use Cheerios, Kix and Rice Krispies.

title: pink fluff pudding
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 1 cup hot water, then add 1 cup cold water.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for about 1 1/2 hours.
When softly jelled, remove and beat in large bowl of electric mixer on high speed for about 5 minutes or until mixture is liquidy.
Beat egg whites in small bowl until peaks are formed, then add to jello mixture and blend well.
Place in refrigerator to set (about 2 hours).

title: blueberry buckle
directions: 1. Mix sugar, soft margarine, eggs, and milk. Then mix flour, baking powder, ands salt.
2. Add dry ingredients slowly to wet ingredients. Mix well
then stirin blueberries.
3. Place in 9 x 11 baking dish. Mix struesel topping and
sprinkle on top of cake mixture before baking.
4. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: "a b c" - aquebogue barbecued chicken
directions: In a bowl, blend all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Pour sauce over chicken, turning to coat evenly with sauce.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes in 400° oven. Uncover, baste with sauce and continue baking 15 minutes.
Broil 5 minutes, basting with sauce until desired crispness is obtained.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and set in refrigerator for 30 minutes to 1 hour. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: delicious dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Great on celery, carrots, crackers, chips, etc.

title: homemade rolls
directions: In a small bowl, put yeast with lukewarm water; set aside.
In a large bowl, put the salt, sugar, oil, hot water and cold water. Mix and then add dissolved yeast and water from small bowl.
Sift a little at a time, the 4 to 5 cups flour, working well with a spoon until all liquid has been absorbed.
Sift 1/2 to 1 cup flour on table or cabinet top.
Place dough on floured surface and knead for about 20 minutes.
Put dough back into bowl.
Rub top with high grade oil (Crisco).
Cover with a dry cloth and let rise until at least double in bulk.

title: hot asparagus canapes
directions: Trim the crust from the bread and flatten the bread with a rolling pin.
Blend cheese and egg to a workable consistency and spread evenly on each slice.
Roll an asparagus in each slice of bread.
Dip each roll in the melted butter until thoroughly coated.
Place the rolls on a cookie sheet and freeze.
When rolls are frozen, slice each into 3 sections and refreeze until needed. To serve, place on a cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Do not thaw before baking.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a Bundt cake pan.
Place biscuit pieces in pan.
Melt margarine; stir in white sugar.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon to mixture and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When done, turn out like a cake and pinch off bite-size pieces.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Line bottom with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk according to label.
Mix in thawed whipped topping.
Prepare frosting from remaining ingredients; set aside.
Pour half the pudding mix over graham crackers.
Top with remaining pudding mix.
Put third layer of whole crackers to cover pudding.
Spread frosting over top layer of crackers. Refrigerate.
Try to leave it in the refrigerator at least 24 hours.

title: czechoslovakian cabbage soup
directions: Place beef bones, onion, carrots, garlic and bay leaf in roasting pan.
Top with short ribs; sprinkle with thyme and paprika.
Roast, uncovered, in 450° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, or until meat is brown.
Transfer meat and vegetables into large kettle.
Using small amount of water, scrape browned bits from roasting pan into kettle.
Add water, cabbage, tomatoes, salt and Tabasco.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Skim off fat.
Add parsley, lemon juice, sugar and sauerkraut (with juice). Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Remove bones and short ribs from kettle.
Cool slightly.
Remove meat from bones and cut into cubes.
Return to kettle and cook 5 minutes longer.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
In a large bowl, mix the broccoli, rice, onion, cheese, garlic powder and soup.
Place in buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal date cookies
directions: Chop dates; sift flour with soda, salt and spices into bowl. Blend in rolled oats, sugar and nuts.
Beat eggs with fork.
Add oil, buttermilk, dates and vanilla.
Pour into dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Press flour, margarine and nuts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely and make next layer.

title: guacamole dip
directions: In small bowl, combine refried beans and chilies.
Spread on large serving plate.
Combine sour cream and taco seasoning. Spoon over bean mixture spreading evenly.
In small bowl, mash avocados.
Stir in ReaLime brand and salts; spoon evenly over sour cream mixture.
Cover; chill several hours.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Blend milk with peanut butter and add to dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set.

title: drunken cake
directions: Mix together and bake in a loaf pan for 40 minutes or an angel food pan for 50 minutes at 350°. Spray pan with Pam.
Cool before taking out of pan.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Lightly salt mushroom caps.
Mix cream cheese, scallions, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Fill mushrooms with mixture. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Broil 5 minutes and serve.
Yields 30 to 36 mushrooms.

title: asparagus frittata
directions: Combine the eggs, Hollandaise sauce, milk, and lemon pepper seasoning.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Saute the onions and bell pepper in the roasted garlic butter and oil until soft but not browned.
Stir in the ham and asparagus.
Pour egg mixture over the top.
Reduce heat to low and cover.
Cook for about 8 to 10 minutes or until the center is set.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover.
Turn off heat.
The heat from the frittata will melt the cheese.
Cut into large squares and serve with additional Hollandaise sauce, if desired.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together lettuce, tomato, onion, beans, cheese and avocado. Place Fritos and hamburger in separate bowls so that everyone can add the amount they want. Top with dressing.

title: crabmeat snack
directions: Melt butter.
Add cheese and other ingredients.
(Add drained crabmeat last.)
Split muffins in half and spread with mixture. Put in freezer until firm (about 30 minutes).
Remove and cut each half into 6 equal parts.
Freeze until solid and put in freezer bags.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cook the rice according to directions.
Saute chopped onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and bake until bubbly about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Soft melt margarine in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Stir in uncooked macaroni; coat well.
Add salt, pepper and cheese; mix well and spread evenly.
Slowly pour in milk.
With bottom of spoon, push macaroni down under milk.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or until macaroni is done and custard set.
Cubed ham may be added to this for a one dish meal.

title: cornmeal english muffins
directions: In a small saucepan, heat milk until bubbles appear around side of pan; remove from heat and add margarine.
Set aside to allow butter to melt and mixture to cool to warm (105° to 115°).

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Parboil broccoli enough to thaw.
Put in cheese to melt. Mix all in baking dish at 350° for 1/2 hour or until it bubbles.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow casserole.
Mix sour cream and soup; pour over chicken.
Mix crumbs, butter and poppy seed.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
If desired, you can use 2 cans soup, 1 cup Ritz crackers and 1 1/2 sticks butter.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, dry jello, pineapple and Cool Whip together and chill.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Pour sugar into large bowl.
Add butter, milk and cocoa.
Do not stir.
Place in microwave oven for 2 1/2 minutes or until margarine melts.
Take bowl out of oven and add nuts and vanilla; stir well.
Pour into dish.
Place in freezer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar, dill, basil and oregano; let stand, then add the following: torn lettuce, cucumbers, onion and peas.
After these are layered, spread mayonnaise mixture over like frosting.
Chill in refrigerator as long as possible to blend flavors (prepare the day before to be at its best).
Will stay super crisp.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Stir in mayonnaise and hot pepper sauce; mix well. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving. Yield: 10 servings.

title: yellow layer cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add baking powder to flour; stir to blend.
Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla (beginning and ending with dry ingredients).
Pour into 2 greased wax paper-lined 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on racks for 5 minutes before removing from pans.

title: recipe for living
directions: Combine and spread out to allow flowers and leaves time to dry, approximately 2 weeks, 6 teaspoons rose oil or your favorite potpourri refresher oil may be added.
Seal in a plastic bag for 2 to 3 days so the flowers will absorb the oil.
It is now ready to be placed in lace handkerchief as favors or showered on the Bride and Groom.

title: honey balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter, honey and nonfat dry milk (solid). Then form into balls.
Crush graham crackers.
Then roll butter balls into graham crackers.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar; mix in flour and milk until smooth. Pour in peaches and juice. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with milk, lemon juice and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Spread on cherry filling and serve.
Serves 8.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar; cream until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted flour and milk alternately. Bake in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir beef in 2 tablespoons of margarine or butter in 10-inch skillet over low heat until brown.
Reserve 1/3 cup of the bouillon. Stir remaining bouillon, the catsup, garlic and salt into skillet.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in mushrooms and onion.
Cover and simmer until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.

title: plains, georgia, cheese ring
directions: Combine all ingredients, except preserves; season to taste with pepper.
Mix well and place in ring mold.
Refrigerate overnight. To serve, unmold and, if desired, fill center with strawberry preserves or serve plain with crackers.
Makes enough for a large group or may be halved and served in a half-circle around a small bowl of preserves.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and creamy.
Add soda and flavorings, then add alternately eggs and small amount of flour and sour cream until all ingredients are used.
Mix just until well blended.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into 3-quart tube pan that has been greased and dusted with flour.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.
(This has a crunch top which makes it different from most pound cakes.)

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Pour over beans and onion. Refrigerate overnight and serve.

title: cindi's yummy sweet rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare rice as directed on package.

title: cheeseburger pasta
directions: Add to cooked beef, soups, water and pasta. Heat to a boil. Cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until done, stirring often.

title: oven fried garlic chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a shallow bowl, blend together bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
In a small saucepan, heat butter and garlic over very low heat until butter melts. Remove from heat.
Brush chicken pieces with garlic butter, then roll in bread crumb mixture to coat.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Soften	yeast
in
warm
water.
Scald milk; add sugar, salt and

Add
cup
flour and beat thoroughly.
Add
egg
