Add enough more flour to make soft dough.
Turn dough out onto board and knead until
smooth
and	satin, about 10 minutes.
Put into greased container and
cover;
let	rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Knead
down and make out rolls.
Let rise until double. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kay's famous fettuccini
directions: Melt the margarine in a skillet and saute the onion and bell pepper until both are tender.
Add flour and stir well.
Do not brown.
Gradually add the cream and cheese.
Add the seasonings and shrimp.
Cook the fettuccini in a separate pot accordingly to the package directions.
Drain.
Pour shrimp mixture over the fettuccini and serve.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, rice, soup and 1/2 cup onions.
Cover with vented plastic.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes.
Microwave cheese according to label.
Stir cheese spread into broccoli.
Top with onions.
Microwave 2 minutes, or until heated.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: salsa
directions: Remove seeds from the chilies.
Blend first 3 ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: hamburger and noodles
directions: Fry onion with ground beef until brown.
Stir in cooked noodles.
Mix together with ground beef, cheese and tomato sauce. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: cry babies (molasses cookies)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, and molasses.
Add eggs and spices and vanilla; beat well.
Then add soda to the coffee and stir in vinegar.
Add salt and flour and blend well. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees 10 to 12 minutes.

title: frenz
directions: P.S.
It is important to hav frenz in the wrld.
A sponfol ov fun.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Heat milk, cheese and salad dressing over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Add small amount of asparagus juice to mushroom soup.
Layer ingredients in 2-quart size casserole dish.
Repeat until dish is full.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in 300° to 350° oven until hot and cheese is melted.

title: easy basic sandwich bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and yeast together.
Add water and stir until smooth (about 2 minutes).
Mix in additional flour, one cup at a time.
The third cup should be kneaded in until dough is elastic.
Pour small amount of oil on dough.
Let stand in warm spot to rise until doubled (about 40 minutes).
Divide the dough in half and knead each half until smooth and formed into loaf. Place in greased pan and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: marinade for beef
directions: Sprinkle meat with meat tenderizer.
Cover with sauce. Refrigerate for 4 hours before cooking.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: jellied cranberry salad
directions: Combine sour cream, cream cheese and sugar until well blended with electric mixer.
Stir in cranberry, pineapple and pecans. Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in lightly oiled 6-cup mold or bowl and freeze.
If using bowl, do not oil.
This salad should be only slightly thawed before serving.
Can be used with entrees or for dessert.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix
together butter, mustard, poppy seed, mayonnaise and onion. Spread on
half
of open bun.
Add ham and cheese slice. Wrap in foil. Bake at
325° for 20 minutes.
May be made ahead, frozen and then baked at 300°
for
minutes.
I
sometimes use
celery seed in a smaller amount rather than poppy seed.

title: trifle spectacular
directions: Cut one cake layer into 1-inch cubes.
Freeze other cake layer for later use.
Combine sweetened condensed milk and water in a large bowl.
Stir until blended.
Add pudding mix; beat until thoroughly blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold whipped cream into pudding mixture.

title: greatest pie crust
directions: Add together dry ingredients and shortening (mix to pea size). Put 1 egg in measuring cup, then add water to it to make 3/4 cup. Add vinegar.
Beat together.
Add to dry ingredients; mix and roll out.
Makes 4 pies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook in skillet: oleo, onion, celery and broccoli.
Add next 3 ingredients and cook in casserole dish, covered with foil, for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, butter and vanilla; mix until fluffy. Gradually add sugars and mix well. Add chocolate chips and mix until well blended. Cover and chill for 2 hours. Form into a ball and roll in crushed pecans. Serve with graham crackers.

title: pralines
directions: Mix sugar, milk, baking soda and corn syrup.
Cook to a soft ball, stirring constantly.
Add pecans, butter and vanilla.
Beat until firm enough to drop from spoon on wax paper.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, combine oats, sugars, flour and salt.
Combine soda and water; stir into oats mixture along with shortening and vanilla.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from oven; allow to stand 2 minutes before removing to wire rack to cool.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: homemade seasoned salt
directions: Mix all together and store in airtight container.

title: new england maple ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients except ribs; cook until heated through and pour over ribs.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Grill, broil or bake, basting frequently.

title: pusser's painkiller
directions: Mix, pour over ice, sprinkle with Nutmeg on top.

title: skillet salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet and crumble.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and onion to fat in skillet.
Add crumbled bacon.
Heat thoroughly.
Take from stove and toss cabbage and parsley in hot dressing.

title: norma's shrimp dip
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and set aside. Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs, molasses and zucchini. Beat until blended. Add dry ingredients and raisins. Mix well. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Remove at once and store in tight cover containers. Freezes well.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: Cook cauliflower; drain.
Place in baking dish.
Add sour cream and bread crumbs on top.
Place in oven until lightly browned at 350°.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, cocoa, vanilla and milk.
Add beaten eggs (do not beat with mixer).
Pour into crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°; then 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 12 hours and serve with raw vegetable sticks and slices.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, put in baking dish.
Pour tomato juice over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, spread catsup on top and let brown for 10 more minutes.

title: meltaway cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large bowl until light.
Gradually add flour, then stir in chips and nuts (if desired).
Roll well rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cookies will be pale.
Let stand for 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheets.
Cool, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: new orleans pepper steak
directions: Prepare the steaks for the grill about 1/2 hour ahead of time. Rub the two steaks with all of the ingredients using 1/2 for each steak.
Grill over hot coals to desired degree of doneness.
The amount of pepper used can be varied according to your taste but do not increase the amount of garlic.
The garlic cooks with the steaks and will not be overwhelming.
Serve with the Steak Butter recipe given below.
This is a slightly spicy variation on steak that still does not mask the taste of good beef.

title: roman holiday
directions: Lightly brown onions in fat in a large skillet; add hamburger and cook until browned.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Have Dutch oven ready; add a layer of spaghetti, then add the meat mixture and layer of cheese.
Repeat layers and top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Dot with oleo.
Cover and cook at 300° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Line 11 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Pour in batter made by combining above ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Do not over bake.

title: custard pie
directions: Make pastry for 1 crust pie; line pie pan.
Build up high fluted edge.
For a 9-inch pie, beat eggs, then add sugar, salt, nutmeg, hot milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla, if desired.
Pour into pastry-lined pan.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake just until silver knife inserted 1-inch from side of filling comes out clean. Center will look soft, but will set later.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in greased baking dish.
Bake in 350° over for about 45 minutes.
As it browns, stir several times.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk, sugar and whipped topping.
Pour on bottom of pan.
Mix milk, pudding, pumpkin, cinnamon and cloves. Pour on top of first mixture.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Top with whipped topping.

title: chow mein noodle hot dish
directions: Brown together the ground beef, onion and celery.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot brunswick stew
directions: Start in crock-pot on high, then turn to low.
Stir once in awhile.
You may add lemon juice and spaghetti noodles during the last hour of cooking.

title: coconut custard yam pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs with sugar, salt and spices.
Add mashed yams and evaporated milk.

Mix well. Fold in 1 cup coconut. Turn into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until tip of knife inserted into center of pie comes out clean. Serve warm or cooled with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: wade's favorite cookies
directions: Cream together all ingredients, except flour, soda, salt and chocolate chips.
Then add chocolate chips. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Makes 1 serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crumble corn chips and put 1/2 in bottom of casserole dish. Slice tamales into chili and heat.
Put 1/2 of chili and tamales over corn chips, then 1/2 of cheese, then remaining corn chips, chili and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Saute sausage in skillet until brown.
Stir until sausage is crumbly.
Drain sausage well.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter in skillet until tender.
Add eggs.
Cook and stir until eggs are set.
Spoon eggs and sausage onto tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Spoon sour cream over cheese.
Arrange tomato on top.
Fold tortillas in half to serve.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted into middle comes out clean.
Place dish in a pan of water while baking as you would any custard.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil confectioners sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, then add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Pour in greased pan.
Cool and cut.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add tomatoes, soup, onion and chili powder.
Cook a little.
Layer in casserole dish with tortillas and cheese.
End with cheese on top.
Heat until cheese melts and heated through at 350°.

title: chicago omelet
directions: Place an 8-inch omelet pan over moderate heat.
Do not overheat or butter will smoke and burn.
Beat eggs, water, salt and pepper thoroughly with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients, except butter. When pan is hot, add butter and stir around quickly to coat bottom of pan.
Pour in egg mixture and shake pan with one hand, stirring mixture with the other.
An omelet should remain soft and creamy in the center.
To turn out of pan, hold handle.
If a filling is used, place a small amount in upper half of omelet.
Raise pan to a 45° angle and using a fork, start to roll omelet from the top down. Turn onto a warm plate and serve immediately.
Makes 1 serving.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and clove of garlic.
Add beans, cheese, chili powder and dash of Tabasco sauce.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pans or use paper baking cups.
Blend, batter will be slightly lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pralines
directions: Butter sides of heavy saucepan.
Combine sugars and milk. Heat and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Increase heat and cook mixture to thread stage.
Remove from heat and add butter and pecans.
Let mixture get almost stiff in pot, then spoon on buttered pan.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: *Optional:
In place of 2 whole eggs, use 3 egg whites.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased casserole dish, make layer of green beans, cream of mushroom soup and onion rings; repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top layer; cover casserole dish and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
(This dish is always requested for potluck parties at work.)

title: shredded beef
directions: Brown chuck roast in oil in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add 1 cup water, cumin and garlic powder.
Simmer until meat is tender enough to pull apart (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Let cool until cool enough to handle.
With hands remove and discard fat, bones and gristle.
Shred remaining lean meat.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch, then add buttermilk, butter, egg yolks and lemon extract. Mix well and cook over low heat, stirring till butter melts and mixture is slightly thickened. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400 degrees till golden brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and softened cream cheese.
Add eggs and vanilla; beating well.
Blend in flour and salt until smooth. Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mashed potato cake
directions: Cream oleo, milk, vanilla, sugar and yolks.
Add 1 cup potatoes.
Sift cocoa, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix with warm milk.
Beat 4 egg whites and fold in.
Add chopped walnuts. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water; bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add into butter mix 6 ounces of the morsels and vanilla; stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add in eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Gradually blend in flour mix.
Stir well.
Add rest of morsels and add nuts. Spread into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely, then cut into sixteen 2 1/4-inch squares.

title: non-bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Measure oatmeal into a bowl; set aside.
Combine sugar, oleo, milk and vanilla in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil 1 minute.
Add peanut butter; stir until dissolved.
Add oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly and let set 1 minute.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Let stand until set.
Nuts may be added if desired.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl. Drop by teaspoon 1-inch apart onto well-greased cookie sheet. Press down ends of coconut with spoon. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Remove immediately and cool on a rack. Makes 4 dozen.

title: pickled red cabbage
directions: Shred red cabbage.
Sprinkle with a little salt and place in bowl.
Combine vinegar, water and sugar in pan and bring to boil. Pour hot liquid over cabbage and refrigerate at least 24 hours. Will keep in the refrigerator at least 2 weeks.

title: kinder-krunchies brew
directions: Pour cranberry juice and apple cider in a punch bowl.
Stir in orange juice concentrate.
Serve over ice.

title: potato "croutons" microwave
directions: In pie plate, toss potatoes with dried bread crumbs, paprika and garlic salt.
Add butter.
Cook on high 6 to 8 minutes stirring occasionally.

title: black bean soup
directions: Stir-fry onions and
garlic
in
margarine
in	a large saucepan over moderate
heat
for
about 10 minutes.
Blend in herbs and sherry;
heat
2	minutes.
Then	add
the remaining ingredients and
simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 1/2 to 3/4 hour, until
flavors are well blended.	Ladle into soup bowls and serve.

title: herbed potato crackers with cheese(yields 8 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brush baking sheet with some melted butter.
With a very sharp knife or a mandoline slicer, thinly cut one unpeeled potato lengthwise into about 24 (1/16-inch thick) slices.
Arrange potato slices on buttered baking sheet and brush top of each with some melted butter.
Place one or two parsley leaves on each potato slice.
Thinly slice remaining potato; place one slice to cover parsley.
Brush top with melted butter.
Bake potato crackers 10 minutes; turn over and bake until golden brown and crisp, about 10 minutes longer.
Arrange crackers on serving plates.
Top each with some goat cheese or cottage cheese spread and serve.
Enjoy!

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and oleo together and press into floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over first mixture.
Bake at 325° to 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top when done or when cool.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Drain string beans.
Place string beans in bottom of dish.
Place mushroom soup next.
(Do not add water to soup as directed on can.)
Place onion rings on top of mushroom soup.
Set oven at 375° and let onion rings brown or get warm.

title: crab muffins
directions: Mix margarine, cheese, mayonnaise and salts together in an electric mixer or food processor.
Add crab; mix and then spread on muffin halves.
Cut each muffin into 4 quarters.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Brown meat with garlic.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add tomato paste and water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Arrange cooked noodles in oiled casserole alternating noodles, sauce and cheese.
Sprinkle grated Romano on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: orange whip
directions: Bring jello and pineapple to a boil.
Cool completely.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry waldorf
directions: Grind cranberries and combine with marshmallows and sugar. Cover and chill overnight.

title: cream gravy for fried poultry
directions: Remove fried poultry to a platter; keep warm.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of the drippings in the skillet.

title: crustless zucchini quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch quiche pan with 1 teaspoon butter. Steam zucchini until very soft (about 10 minutes).
Saute onion in 2 teaspoons butter until transparent. When cool, mix with Ricotta cheese, Cheddar cheese, milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Fold in zucchini and pour into quiche pan.
Bake for about one hour, or until quiche is golden and firm to the touch.
Yields six servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Dry spinach on paper towel and mix all together.
Serve with vegetables and chips.

title: janel's french chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine salt, pepper, flour, powdered milk and sugar in plastic bag.
Shake 2 or 3 pieces of chicken at a time and arrange into greased dish.
Cut butter into small chunks and place on top of individual pieces.
Sprinkle French dressing in a pattern over chicken, sprinkle with paprika.
Cook uncovered in a 350° oven for 1 hour until chicken is done.

title: seafoam lime punch
directions: Cut bananas in 1-inch chunks; place in blender with one cup Gatorade.
Blend at high speed until bananas are pureed.
In punch bowl, combine pureed bananas with other cup of Gatorade, pineapple juice, lemonade concentrate and dry ginger ale.
Add lime sherbet and stir until foamy.
Float lime slices in punch.
Makes 32 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in ungreased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Cook uncovered in a 350° oven until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit salad recipe
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix salad dressing, sugar and milk good, then pour over fruit and stir it up.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cherry mash
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into balls.
Place on plate and put in refrigerator to cool.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Bake the cake according to directions in a 9 by 13 in. pan. Cool on a wire rack for 30 min. and then poke holes with handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour butterscotch syrup over cake.
Mix pudding with 1 c. milk and pour over syrup.
Spread whipped topping over the cake and sprinkle crushed candy over all.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and chill. Good for several days.

title: bayou crawfish
directions: Chop 5 vegetables.
Melt oleo in skillet and add vegetables; saute.
Add cheese until it melts.
Blend flour into mixture.
Add half and half.
Stir in crawfish tails; stir well.
Add parsley and Tony Chachere seasoning.
Cook pasta according to directions and drain.
Add to crawfish mixture.
Put in large casserole.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
This may be made the day before serving, or frozen a week before.
Serves 12.

title: doris archer's irish plum cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; rub in butter.
Add other ingredients and make to a sticky consistency with milk.
Put in a greased 8-inch tin and bake for approximately 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Reduce heat slightly after first 3/4 hour.

title: easy-living lasagna
directions: Microwave crumbled ground beef and onion for 4 to 5 minutes at High until beef is no longer pink.
Drain off fat; stir in seasonings and sugar.
Add spaghetti sauce and water.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Make salad dressing following directions on packet (I use red wine vinegar); set aside.
Wedge tomatoes after peeling.
Peel and slice cucumbers.
Chop scallions.
Place all vegetables in large bowl and pour salad dressing over them.
Chill and serve.

title: tuba toot beans
directions: Mix all and bake 1 hour at 375° or until done.
You may use the microwave; bake 18 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: parmesan vidalia in foil
directions: Will also need heavy duty aluminum foil.

title: buckeyes(peanut butter balls)
directions: Mix peanut butter and margarine with 10x sugar until smooth. Form into balls (size of chestnuts).
Refrigerate overnight. Slowly melt chocolate chips and wax together in double boiler. Using a toothpick, dip cold ball into chocolate until covered. Drop onto wax paper.
Let set.
Touch up spot left by removal of toothpick with a dab of chocolate.
Makes approximately 125 to 150.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given. Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: banana nut raisin bread
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts, then oil and slightly beaten eggs, then bananas.
Bake in a 350° oven in loaf pan for 45 to 60 minutes.
Let cool partially before turning out on rack.

title: sweet caroline cake
directions: No eggs and no milk in this recipe.

title: homemade pizza crust
directions: Mix water and yeast and set aside. Mix flour, oil and salt to 1 cup water.
Add water/yeast mixture to flour mixture and mix together. Pour out on floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise for approximately 20 minutes.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain off fat.
Separate dough into 8 triangles; place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press to form a crust; seal.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: berks potato filling
directions: Thoroughly mix the mashed potatoes and eggs, using a fork. Add milk and set aside.
Cut the bread into 1/2-inch cubes and brown with the onions in the butter.
Stir onions and bread into the potato mixture; add seasoning.
Turn into a greased casserole and bake for an hour in a 375° oven.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet and drain.
Mix all ingredients together, pouring 1/2 into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Alternating mixture and cheese with cheese ending up on top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: spaghetti with tomatoes, salami and green olives
directions: Puree tomatoes; push through sieve into a saucepan.
Add oregano, salami and olives; heat gently.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: madrigal marinated carrots(serves 50)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add onions and green peppers. Heat remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Marinate 12 hours or more.
Drain to serve.
Serve hot or cold.

title: blueberry pineapple cream
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Toast cornflake crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken puff bravo
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine process cheese spread, sour cream and garlic salt; stir over low heat until process cheese spread is melted.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks thoroughly; reserve 1 tablespoon for glaze.
Gradually stir remaining egg yolks into cheese mixture.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into cheese mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: dream whip pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes. Add ice; stir continuously until gelatin is thickened, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whip, blend gelatin and Cool Whip until smooth.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add flour and nuts, then vanilla.
Roll between hands to shape fingers.
Bake at 300° until brown around edge.
Roll in 10x sugar while hot.

title: weight watchers chili
directions: In large skillet, cook ground turkey until gray.
Do not overcook.
Drain well.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer until onions are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken enchilada casserole(good with mexican salad)
directions: Boil chicken and cut up. Preheat oven to 350°. Mix soups and chiles together. Saute onion, then mix with soups. Add chicken. Butter a 9 x 13 pan. Put a layer of halved taco shells or tortilla chips. Pour in half of mixture. Put layer of cheese on top. Add the rest of the mixture and another layer of cheese. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Butter sides and bottom of pan.
Generously mix 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and walnuts; sprinkle a fine layer of sugar, cinnamon and nuts on bottom of pan, then a layer of dough and so forth until all the ingredients are gone.
Bake in oven approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; pour into greased pan, 9 x 13-inch. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 1/2 cups of chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken stuffed with rice
directions: Cook rice.
To rice add onions, green pepper, tomato, salt and pepper.
Toss well.
Stuff breasts (secure with toothpicks, if needed).
Place in baking dish or pan.
Mix together mushroom soup, water and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: greek style leg of lamb
directions: Wash meat and place in roasting pan.
Make incisions in the lamb in several places and insert cloves of garlic.
Rub lemon juice over entire roast, then salt, pepper and oregano.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
After the meat has browned, turn over to brown back side.
Potatoes and carrots may be added, with a small amount of water after lamb has been cooking one hour.
(Add more water if evaporated.)

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl
Keeps up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Can be frozen.

title: rum cake
directions: Spray a Bundt pan with Pam.
Combine all cake ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into cake pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese, eggs, vanilla, sugar and lemon juice until light and fluffy.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Serve with your favorite topping.

title: rice salad ii
directions: Bring to a boil 1 cup water and add rice.
Simmer about 5 minutes until water is absorbed.
Let cool and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in long dish in order listed.
Chill, if desired and serve.
Refrigerate.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Mix and pour on top of	mixture in pan.
Bake 25 minutes longer at 350°.
Purple plums can be
used and it is not necessary to peel them.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo or butter until onions are wilted.
Blend flour in well with this mixture.
Pour in milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks, salt, red and black pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Put crabmeat in a bowl suitable for mixing and pour the cooked sauce over the crabmeat.
Blend well and then transfer into a lightly greased casserole and sprinkle with grated American cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Serves 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chop onion, green pepper and eggs.
Mix with chopped chicken, salad dressing and relish.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: full meal casserole
directions: Place the toast in a large shallow casserole.
Cook asparagus according to package directions.
Place alternate layers of chicken and asparagus over the toast.
Mix chicken soup with water and pour over toast, chicken and asparagus.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover top with cheese and bake until cheese is melted. Serves 6.

title: cheesy micro fries
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 12-inch glass dish.
Cut potatoes in wedges.
Coat with margarine.
Combine remaining ingredients. Sprinkle over potatoes.
Cover with paper towels.
Microwave on Full for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes.

title: corn meal dumplings
directions: Beat egg.
Add to it the milk, flour and baking powder together.
Add corn meal.
Add the liquids to dry ingredients and drop by spoonfuls into boiling hot soup or stew.
Cover tightly and cook 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna patio salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions. Drain. Combine macaroni, tuna, tomatoes, mushrooms, cucumber, celery, green onion and green pepper.
Blend Italian dressing, sour cream, seasoned salt and pepper.
Toss with macaroni mixture.
Chill. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: russie's special
directions: Lay meat and cheese on flat tortilla.
Microwave 55 seconds. (That's what he said!) Remove and fold over.
Chow down.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix eggs, butter and sugar. You can use 1/2 box of light brown sugar and 1/2 box of confectioners sugar in place of 1 box of light brown sugar. Add flour, coconut, vanilla and pecans. Press in sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour. (Don't overbake.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Chill.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and sprinkle in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (save 3 tablespoons for top of cake).
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add Milnot, a little at a time.
Mix Jell-O with hot water; set until starting to jell good.
Add crushed pineapple. Whip all together; pour over crumb mixture. Sprinkle top with rest of crumbs and chill.

title: pizza dip
directions: Bake breadsticks as directed on package.
Cut into 2-inch pieces; set aside.
In bowl, mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with pizza sauce. Place pizza topping on top of sauce; cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.
Remove from oven and use breadsticks to dip.

title: almond bars
directions: Mix all together in a bowl, flour, sugar, baking powder, almonds, eggs and oil; mix well.
Roll in 6 strips, bake in slightly greased pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Brush with egg, cut while warm.

title: marble squares
directions: Combine butter, water and chocolate in saucepan; bring to boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in combined flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add eggs and sour cream; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing until well blended.
Blend in egg.
Spoon over chocolate batter.
Cut through with knife several times for marble effect.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: oven meatballs
directions: Combine milk, onion, eggs and salt.
Add bread crumbs and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add meat and mix thoroughly.
Shape into 4 dozen small balls.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: six cup fruit salad
directions: Gently toss all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.
One cup sliced green grapes may be substituted for the oranges.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats with margarine.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir gently all together; bake in loaf pan 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Melt butter in medium size iron skillet.
Add sugar, mixing well.
Slowly add cream, stirring constantly.
Add some of the hot mixture to the well beaten egg and stir in.
Cook slowly until consistency of custard.
Set aside to cool.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients.
Drop in ungreased muffin tins.
Full tins 3/4 full and bake for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 12 large muffin biscuits.

title: golden punch
directions: Blend on high all ingredients for 15 to 20 seconds.
Add ginger ale last.
Chill.

title: crab and cheese triangles
directions: Mix crab, cheese and butter together.
Spread on English muffins thick.
Cut into fourths.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: tea cakes(about 60)
directions: Sift flour and baking
powder
together twice.	Mix all ingredients and chill 1 hour.
Roll and bake at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Pour into large bowl and add any flavor of sherbet; float small scoops on top of liquid.
Very refreshing and easy.

title: praline cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream butter; add brown sugar gradually.
Cream well, then blend in egg, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by tsp. on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 350° for 10-12 minutes.

title: touchdown chocolate bars(makes 24 to 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add egg; mix until well blended. Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture.
Press remainder evenly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
In saucepan, combine Eagle Brand and 1 cup Hershey's chocolate chips. Over low heat, cook and stir until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Spread evenly over prepared crust.
Add nuts and remaining 1 cup Hershey's chocolate chips to reserved crumb mixture; sprinkle evenly over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until center is set. Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store covered at room temperature.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage, hamburger and onion. Drain.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook on high for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Serve with nacho chips.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until hard ball forms in water. Pour gradually over stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly until cool.
Add nuts and continue beating until creamy and stiff enough to drop on wax paper.

title: mexi-chili rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Roll up and place in covered container at least one hour in refrigerator. Slice and serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Dip a glass into sugar, then flatten cookie and put crisscross in with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cabbage scramble
directions: Boil cabbage 10 minutes.
Brown hamburger and onion and season with salt and pepper.
Place ingredients in layers in a large casserole dish or oblong baking pan.
Cover with soup and juice.
Bake at 350° in oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix all the ingredients into a stiff dough. Grease both sides of dough with oil. Cover lightly with foil and allow to stand all day. That night, punch down. Knead 3 or 4 times and divide into 3 loaves.

Lightly knead each loaf 1 to 3 times on a floured surface. Put into greased loaf pans and let rise overnight, covered lightly in oven. The next morning, bake on bottom rack of a 350° oven. Remove and brush with butter, if desired.

title: mississippi mud frosting(very rich and good!)
directions: Cake Layer:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, sugar and cocoa.
Add all other ingredients in order listed.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2 pan for 30 to 40 minutes.
While cake is still hot, gently spread 1 1/4 jars (use 7-ounce jar) Marshmallow Crme on cake. Let cake get cold so Marshmallow Crme will have a crusty top. Gently spread on frosting (follows).

title: ham loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix ingredients well and pack in pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: pork fried rice
directions: In wok or frying pan, cook diced pork 10 minutes in margarine. Add onions and celery.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Scramble eggs and dice. Return all ingredients to frying pan with rice and seasonings. Fry to brown.

title: four chips fudge
directions: Melt butter in a heavy Dutch oven over low heat; stir in sweetened condensed milk and milk.
Add all morsels, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in marshmallow cream and flavorings.
Stir in walnuts.
Spoon into a buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan; spread mixture evenly. Chill and cut into squares.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick margarine and 1 (12 ounce) package chocolate chips; pour over the top and chill.

title: franks family style
directions: In saucepan, cook the onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in soup and water.
In shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch), alternate potatoes, sprinkled with salt and pepper, with soup mixture.
Top with frankfurters, sliced diagonally.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Whisk until completely smooth.
Cover and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
Keeps up to a week.

title: fruit soup
directions: Combine tapioca, sugar (if using substitute, add to tapioca after cooking) and water in a saucepan and allow to stand for a few minutes.
Cook until thick.
Add orange juice, strawberries and oranges.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into a loaf.
Place in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or high for 3 1/2 to 5 hours.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Add cold water to dough until it forms a soft ball.
Flour board and roll out to two 9-inch pie pans.
Puncture with fork. Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Grate the apples (using side of grater on which you shred cabbage).
Pour sugar over grated apples and mix well.
Pour into an uncooked 9-inch pie crust and sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Turn down to 325° and let stay for about 35 minutes more or until done.
Pie has a syrupy or glazed effect.
Top with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: james' broccoli soup
directions: In large soup pot, cook broccoli in chicken stock with bay leaf until tender, about 20 minutes.
Melt butter, add flour and mix well.
When broccoli is done, remove bay leaf and puree in blender with chicken stock.
Return to pot.
Add butter-flour mixture, parsley, thyme, sage, pepper and Worcestershire sauce; stir until blended.
Heat on low.

title: banana-bran bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using solid vegetable shortening, thoroughly grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan; set aside.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cut up the fruit of your choice and enjoy!

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch pan with oleo, use largest recipe on back of the instant potatoes and prepare potatoes as directed.
Top with sour cream after potatoes have cooled.
Top with bacon and the green onions, cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° or 350°, approximately 30 minutes, until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: roast beef and yorkshire pudding
directions: Pudding:
Place eggs in bowl.
Add milk, flour and salt.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes with rotary beater.
Add oil; beat 30 seconds more (don't overbeat).

title: 1-2-3-4 white cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat with mixer 5 minutes.
Pour in 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: ham-roni-salad
directions: Combine ham, macaroni, celery, carrots, peppers and onions. Combine mayonnaise, barbecue sauce (optional), catsup and mustard. Mix thoroughly and add to other mixture.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick and vanilla.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.
Do not overbake. Makes 5 dozen.

title: pecan toffee(mock almond roca)
directions: Mix butter and sugar in skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly, until lightly browned.
Pour over nuts that have been spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Spread out, then sprinkle chips over and spread when melted with some nuts.
Cool and break in pieces.
Makes 6 x 9-inch sheet.

title: tater bake
directions: Alternately layer potatoes, mushrooms and 1 1/2 cups of cheese in lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Combine heavy cream, parsley, scallions, garlic, sherry, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour over layers.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of remaining cheese and dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 25 minutes longer, until potatoes are tender.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli, grapes, scallions and apple. Cut these ingredients in small pieces. Peel the apple before cutting into small pieces. The red grapes are to be cut in halves. Combine all of these ingredients in medium to large mixing bowl. Add the sliced almonds. Add mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar. Stir all of these ingredients together. Add bacon bits into mixture and stir together. Chill for at least an hour before serving.

title: southern broiled trout
directions: Salt and pepper
trout,
place	in foil.
Mix remaining ingredients, pour over trout, close foil.
Broil at 450° until done.

title: banana pops
directions: Peel bananas and cut in half (across).
Put a popsicle stick into the end of the banana.
Put pops in freezer for one hour . Take pops out and spread honey over them.
Roll each pop in crispy rice cereal.
Ready to eat.

title: layered open faced sandwich(diet)
directions: Layer turkey, cranberry sauce, lettuce and tomato on bread. Top with pickle spear.

title: easy cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water; stir until jello dissolves, then add cold water, pineapple, sugar and cranberry sauce.
Stir well. Add pecans and celery.
Chill.

title: white cream sauce de george
directions: Over low-medium heat, melt butter.
Add flour, stirring continuously until mixed.
Add small amount of half and half (about 4 ounces); mix until smooth.
When this starts to thicken, add other 4 ounces half and half.
When this starts to thicken, add another 4 ounces half and half.
Add salt and pepper.
Set aside. Do not get too thick, but thick.

title: fresh fruit ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an ice cream freezer. Freeze according to freezer instructions.
For vanilla ice cream, omit fruit and food coloring and increase half and half to 4 cups.

title: great muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix dry ingredients.
Add rind, apples or bananas, raisins and pecans.
Set aside.

title: hearty pot roast
directions: In large heavy pan, brown roast in shortening.
Pour off fat. Reserve 3/4 cup broth.
Add remaining broth, Worcestershire sauce, salt and bay leaf to pan.
Cover and cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Cook 1 hour more or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Blend reserved broth with flour until smooth.
Add cinnamon.
Slowly stir into sauce.
Cook until thick.

title: klub(potato dumplings)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pork.
Shape into balls with your hands.
Put small pieces of pork in center of dumpling.
Add enough flour to keep them from sticking.
Drop them into boiling, salted water.
Cover and boil 1 hour.
Stir occasionally to keep them from sticking.
Serve with butter.

title: fruit squares european style
directions: Work the butter and flour like for a pie crust.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet and pat down with spatula.
Retain a little batter and add enough flour to make it thick enough to roll between the palms of hands to make crisscross strips.
Spread fruit preserves over batter and sprinkle the top with nuts, then place the crisscross strips over top.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: strawberry chantilly
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and butter until crumbly.
Stir in walnuts.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Place 2/3 of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place egg whites, sugar, strawberries and lemon juice in a large, deep bowl.
Whip with an electric mixer. Whip the cream until stiff.
Fold into strawberry mixture.
Spread over crumb mixture in baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Freeze for 6 hours or overnight.

title: cranberry apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix apples, 1 1/4 cups sugar, cranberries, tapioca, cinnamon and water in large saucepan.
Let stand 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cook on medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish; dot with 2 tablespoons margarine.

title: passover apple cake
directions: Peel and slice apples (as for pie).
Add a little sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice. Set aside.
Beat 3 eggs and add 1/4 cup sugar and matzo meal.
Fold in apples.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream chili bake
directions: In skillet
brown ground beef;	drain off fat.	Stir in drained beans,
enchilada sauce, the 1 cup shredded cheese and instant minced onion.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie crusts.
Chill and serve.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix well in large bowl.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tin and bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: broccoli-pea casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain. Arrange 1 package broccoli in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with peas.
Combine mushroom soup, mayo, salt, pepper, cheese and eggs to make sauce.
Pour half of sauce over broccoli and peas. Add remaining broccoli and top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix together by hand and drop by teaspoons into small muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen petite biscuits.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Note:
This is a
recipe that comes from my grandmother and is very Pennsylvania Dutch.

title: chunky potato soup
directions: Boil potato cubes until soft (about 15 to 20 minutes).
In a large pot, heat margarine and saute chopped onions until soft. Add milk and flour; heat a few minutes until boiling.
Mix in potatoes, ham and peas; lower heat.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Serves 6 to 8.
This recipe can easily be halved.

title: fast starter(drink)
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender. Run on high until smooth and well blended.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; add flour and nuts.
Mix to make crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remaining crumbs into an 8-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Blend sugar with cream cheese until smooth.
Add egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes more.

title: angel pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy and add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff or holds a peak.
Gradually add sugar; add vanilla and chopped pecans.
Fold in cracker crumbs.
Pour into slightly buttered pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool and cover with Whipped Cream Topping.

title: bread (easy rolls)
directions: Put flour and sugar in large bowl; cut Crisco in.
Mix yeast in warm water; add to mixture.
Add buttermilk and mix well.

title: tuna bake with cheese swirls
directions: Cook onions and peppers in oil until golden brown.
Add salt and flour; blend.
Add soup and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Add tuna and lemon juice.
Pour into baking dish and cover with cheese swirls.
Bake in oven at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce to 425° and bake 15 minutes more.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased (or spray with nonstick spray) 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Brown 1 1/2 cups coconut in margarine.
Add nuts.
Toss in Rice Krispies.
Melt chocolate chips; add evaporated milk and marshmallows.

title: chicken barley stew
directions: In Dutch oven or large saucepan combine tomatoes with their liquid, celery, carrots, chicken broth, 1 cup water, onion, barley, parsley, basil, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Cover.
Place on medium-high heat and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Add chicken to mixture.

title: fortune cookies
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Add sugar until thick and ivory colored. Add 2 teaspoons of water.
Gradually add in cornstarch and stir until smooth.
Drop teaspoonfuls of batter 4-inches in diameter into frying pan with oil.
(Should look like mini pancakes.)
Fry until golden brown.
Remove cookie.
Place fortune on top of cookie. Fold in half, then bend edges.

title: caramelized almonds
directions: Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Spoon onto waxed paper and cool.
Break apart.
Store in an airtight container. These are wonderful on salads or just for eating.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, cream cheese and taco mix.
Spread in pan or bowl.
Spread Cheddar cheese on top. Then spread lettuce, tomatoes and olives on top.

title: famous seafood batter
directions: Mix yeast and flour.
Combine egg, hot water and salt.
Add cold water.
Combine with dry mixture; stir.
Drop fish into batter and immediately drop battered fish into hot oil.
Do not drain fish.

title: broccoli noodle soup
directions: Boil water.
Add bouillon and stir.
Add noodles and rest of ingredients.
Cook until noodles are done.
For thicker soup, add more noodles and cheese.
Serves 6.

title: mile high pink pie
directions: In large skillet, over medium heat, melt butter.
Add coconut. Cook, stirring frequently, until golden brown.
In a 9-inch pie plate, press toasted coconut evenly on bottom of pan and sides to form crust.
Chill.
Pour milk into large bowl and freeze 1 hour, until crystals form.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together.
Beat eggs; add milk and mix. Stir in melted oleo.
Pour into sugar mix and beat until smooth; add vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then bake at 250° for 45 more minutes.

title: black-eyed peas and okra
directions: In a large pot put black-eyed peas, lima beans, okra and ham hock.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender and ham hock is done. Serve over white rice.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Place ingredients in a jar and shake well.
No cooking needed.

title: apple streusel cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread apple pie filling in buttered 9-inch square baking pan.
In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add sweetened condensed milk, melted butter, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Pour over apple filling.
In medium bowl, combine sugar and flour; cut in cold butter until crumbly.
Add nuts and oats. Sprinkle over custard.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until set.
Cool. Serve warm with ice cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Can be microwaved.
If it seems dry, I add a little milk.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Mix together and chill until firm.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Mix above and serve.

title: blueberry supreme
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Chill. Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Spread Cool Whip over pecans.
Top with pie filling. Chill overnight.

title: stewed fig sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a small heavy saucepan.
Over medium-high heat, bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Turn the heat to low.
Cover, simmer, stirring frequently, until figs are tender.
Serve as a compliment to meats, breakfast or dessert dishes.

title: crawfish or shrimp fettucini
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add parsley, crawfish or shrimp and garlic.
Cook 10 minutes on medium fire.
Add cheese, cream and flour (mix flour and cream before).
Simmer 30 minutes. Boil noodles about 10 minutes from time it comes to boil.
Grease a casserole dish or pan with margarine.
Mix noodles and crawfish or shrimp and pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated American cheese if desired, not necessary.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 8 to 12.

title: party chicken
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with dried beef pieces.
Place chicken breasts in pan and on each, place 1/2 strip bacon.
Pour over that the mushroom soup and sour cream.
Bake for 3 hours at 275°, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: salad for traveling
directions: Tear lettuce and place in 18 x 9-inch dish; add celery, onion, pepper, peas and water chestnuts.
Mix sugar with mayonnaise and spread over salad mixture.
Cover with grated cheese and chill overnight.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Place the rhubarb and sugar in saucepan and cook until thick, stirring constantly. Add the jello.
Mix well.
Pour into jelly glasses and cover.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Heat oil in

Dutch oven. Cut tortillas into strips and add to the oil, cooking 2 minutes until crisp. Add onion, jalapenos and garlic. Saut 3 minutes. Add tomato paste and canned tomatoes. Bring to a simmer. Cook 10 minutes. Stir in cumin, cooked shredded chicken, broth, avocado and shredded cheese. Bring to a boil. Turn heat to low and simmer, uncovered, 40 minutes. Will reduce to about 8 cups. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mark's salsa burgers
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients in with ground beef.
Shape into patties.
Place on grill or into frying pan.
Cook about 10 minutes on each side.
Top with cheese for a great burger. Mexican style!

title: mock marshmallow frosting
directions: Place flour
in
a small saucepan.
Add milk gradually, stirring
constantly
until
mixture
is
smooth
and blended. Place mixture
over moderately low heat (about 225°) and cook, stirring
constantly,
until
thickened
and smooth.
(Mixture will be
fairly
stiff.) Cool.
Place butter in the small bowl of an
electric mixer and beat until creamy.
Add sugar gradually and beat
until
mixture is light.
Add the cooled flour mixture and beat
at high speed until the mixture is light and fluffy, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Gently fold in vanilla.
Makes enough to frost the top of a 9-inch cake.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese per package instructions, then add tuna fish, milk, soup and peas; mix all together.
Bake in casserole dish (13 x 9-inch) for 20 minutes.

title: chile corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, soda and salt.
Mix corn, oil, milk and eggs. Combine the mixtures.
Add chiles and cheese; mix well.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in greased, uncovered casserole or favorite baking pan.

title: easy barbecued pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Season chops with salt.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top each pork chops with an onion slice and lemon slice.
Place 1 tablespoon of brown sugar and 1 tablespoon of catsup on top of each chop.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, basting occasionally.

title: egg and sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients including sausage.
Chill for 12 hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken breast halves and water to cover in a medium saucepan; cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until chicken is done; drain well.
Remove chicken from bone; coarsely chop chicken.

title: chowder
directions: Prepare vegetables.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine; add vegetables and saute until slightly soft (5 to 10 minutes). Meanwhile, cut hot dogs into 1/4-inch pennies.
Add meat, soup and milk to pan with vegetables.
Heat about 10 minutes.
Add cheese; let rest a few minutes to soften and partially melt cheese.
Serve with crisp crackers.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In big pan, melt butter on high.
In bowl, mix sugar and cocoa and pour into butter.
Add 1/2 cup milk fast.
Stir quickly. Bring to boil and boil 1 to 2 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add vanilla and oats.
Stir well.
Add peanut butter last.
Drop on aluminum foil.
Let cool.

title: delicious rolls
directions: Dissolve and stir thoroughly the yeast cakes in warm water; set aside.
Mix sugar and Crisco with boiling water; set aside to cool.
When thoroughly cooled, add eggs.
Mix yeast into this. Add flour last.
Be sure not to let yeast touch hot water. Refrigerate overnight.
Make out rolls; let rise until they are double in size.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: oven barbecued ribs
directions: In Dutch oven, add salted water to ribs to cover.
Cover pan and simmer until almost tender, about 1 hour.
Drain and place in shallow baking pan.
In saucepan, combine 1 cup water, 1/2 teaspoon salt, catsup and next 6 ingredients.
Bring to boil. Cook, stirring for 5 minutes.
Add onion and lemon.
Cool.
Spoon over ribs.
Cover.
Chill up to 24 hours.
Bake ribs uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Baste often.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip gillette cookies
directions: Mix eggs, butter and both sugars.
Add vanilla.
Slowly add flour.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake in a waffle iron. Spray waffle iron with Pam.
Let waffle iron preheat about 10 to 15 minutes or about 270°.
Put on iron with teaspoon.
It will take probably 3 to 4 minutes or to a very light brown.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Put flour in one pie plate, bread crumbs in the other and beat egg, oil and water in the 3rd one.
Roll pork chops (each one) in flour first, then egg mixture and then bread crumbs.
Do chops on both sides.
Put the wire rack across your sink and place each pork chop on the rack to dry after you have rolled it in the bread crumbs, 1/2 hour to dry.

title: cube steak and gravy
directions: Place steak and soup in crock-pot.
Cook until done.
Soup makes gravy.

title: chili con queso
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Prepare as you would for tacos following the directions on the taco seasoning packet.
Slice velveeta cheese in chunks and put into large saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup of taco sauce and 1/2 cup milk.
Heat to melting point.
Add hamburger.
Taste and add more hot sauce if preferred.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger lightly; add onions and garlic. Cook until onions are soft. Add spices; simmer 1 hour.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup hot water. Stir in pie filling.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Chill until almost set. Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Beat cream cheese (room temperature) and mayonnaise together.

Slowly add lemon Jell-O and mix well. Stir in undrained pineapple. Fold Cool Whip and marshmallows into lemon mixture. After this has almost set, pour over raspberry and cherry mixture. Sprinkle chopped pecans on top, if desired.
Return to refrigerator and chill until set.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Put chicken, water, salt and pepper into crock-pot.
Simmer, covered, for 4 hours.

title: glazed orange ham
directions: Place ham in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with orange slices.
Combine brown sugar and seasoning.
Sprinkle mix over oranges.
Pour orange juice over ham.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer; baste frequently. Garnish with cherries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: amalgamation cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add yolks, jam and other ingredients with flour, spice and soda that have been sifted together.
Fold in beaten whites. Bake at 300°.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed.
When set, whip in cream cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Sprinkle Crunchus coconut on top. Fill two graham cracker pie shells.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: refrigerated mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes in salted water until tender.
Drain. Beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.
Put in covered container in refrigerator.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks.
When ready to use, put desired amount in greased (or sprayed with Pam) casserole dish.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350°
until heated through.
Makes 8 cups or 12 servings.

title: chocolate frosting mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small mixing bowl.
Mix well. Spread frosting over marshmallows.
Layer on warm cake.

title: cobbler
directions: Bake at 350°
until golden brown, approximately 30 minutes. May need to broil for a few minutes to get desired golden brown.

title: strawberry dessert(servings: 10)
directions: Crumble 1/2 of cake in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix lemon juice with Eagle Brand.
Add berries and Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over cake crumbs.
Add rest of cake crumbs and top with remaining mix.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: punch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Add cold ginger ale when ready to serve. Serves 60 to 65.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat egg until light.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and roll in balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes until lightly brown.

title: ton cake
directions: Pour cans of pie filling in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour dry cake mix over this. In a small saucepan, melt oleo and brown sugar; stir in nuts. Pour over top without stirring. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: In a cake pan, dump pie filling and spread out.
Dump pineapple in and mix together.
Spread out.
Dump dry yellow cake mix on top and spread out.
(Do not mix with filling, this is your topping.)
Slice oleo on top and sprinkle on nuts, if used.
Bake at 325° until crust is golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until firm or set.

title: hidden valley chicken
directions: Mix butter, pepper sauce, vinegar and paprika.
Dip chicken in mixture and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 package of dry dressing mix and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: copper pennies
directions: Put tomato soup, vegetable oil, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and mustard in pot and bring to a boil. Add carrots, onion and peppers and marinate.

title: hot hominy
directions: Mix drained hominy, sour cream
and Cheez Whiz and a very few hot peppers, chopped.
Or you may use the cheese that
has hot peppers already in it, however this makes the dish very highly seasoned.
Bake in 350°
oven 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Pour water over yeast and set aside.
Combine milk, sugar, salt and butter in saucepan.
Heat until lukewarm and butter melts.
In large mixing bowl, beat the egg.
Add the yeast and milk mixtures with 1 cup of flour; beat well.
Add enough more flour to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth.
Place in a greased bowl and cover.
Place in refrigerator overnight or several hours.

title: onion rice casserole
directions: Saute
onions
in margarine.
Combine rice, onion, half and half
and
cheese.	Place
in
9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sirloin kabobs
directions: Combine soy sauce, brown sugar, oil, ginger, mustard, pepper and garlic.
Mix well.
Add meat and let stand 2 hours.
Drain and reserve marinade.
Thread meat on skewers alternating with vegetables.
Broil over hot coals 5 to 6 minutes, turning frequently and basting with marinade; or broil in oven 3 to 5 minutes from heat until crispy brown.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken, debone and save broth.
Add deboned chicken to cooked spaghetti.
(Drain most of broth from spaghetti.)
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add tomatoes and cheese. Cover until cheese melts.
Stir and serve.

title: hot sweet mustard
directions: Mix all ingredients, except mayonnaise;
simmer for a couple of minutes.
Let cool, then add the mayonnaise.

title: mushroom snacks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown mushrooms in butter; stir in garlic, salt, onion, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until liquid evaporates.
Separate dough into 2 rectangles.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press dough over bottom and 1/4-inch up sides to form crust.
Spread cream cheese over dough.
Top with mushroom mixture, then Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes.
Cut into desired shapes.
Serve warm.
Makes 2 dozen snacks.

title: orange sherbet ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into ice cream freezer container. Freeze until hard or motor cuts off on electric freezer.

title: brussels sprouts and mushrooms
directions: Clean and slice vegetables.
Place in large pan of salted water and bring to boil.
Add a squeeze of lemon juice and cook for 10 to 12 minutes until tender.
Heat 1/4 cup butter in skillet with a squeeze of lemon juice and cook the mushrooms for 4 minutes.
Drain the sprouts well and turn both vegetables into a warmed serving dish.
Mix and dot remaining butter then squeeze the remainder of lemon juice over top and sprinkle the almonds.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Drain the whole kernel corn and then mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch well-greased dish after sprinkling cheese on top at 350° about 45 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: cherry vanilla freeze
directions: Cut each cherry in half.
Read the directions on the back of the pudding package; follow them to make the pudding, using the milk.
Add the cherries and stir.
Divide the pudding among 4 dessert dishes.
Place in the freezer for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together first three ingredients with hot water, add eggs and blend well.
Add poppy seed last.
Bake at 350° until browned or pick comes out clean.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and 1 cup sugar; add lightly beaten egg yolks, butter, milk and pecans.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes or until thick.
Pour into crust.
Top with meringue:
3 egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: green pea salad
directions: Layer lettuce, peas, eggs and onions.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Top with cheese and bacon or bacon bits.
If kept wrapped, this will keep several days.

title: delicious strawberry, banana, pineapple jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jello with boiling water. Add strawberries, bananas, pineapple, and nuts. Pour 1\2 mixture into glass 9x9 dish. Refrigerate until Jello sets. About an hour or so. Spread sour cream over jello mixture. Top with rest of Jello mixture. Refrigerate until reset.

title: chicken tortilla super bowl stacks
directions: Optional toppings:
sour cream, avocado slices or chopped tomato.

title: lemon or lime pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill for 12 hours.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine the first five ingredients and sift together.
Beat eggs and add rest of ingredients.
Add flour mixture and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done. Frost with Red Velvet Icing.

title: don's beef tenderloin
directions: Purchase 4 to 5 pound beef tenderloin.	Ask butcher to trim and tie the tenderloin. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Over a hot grill, cook about 1 hour (depending on the weather) for medium. Turn about every 5 to 10 minutes. Let it set for about 15 minutes before slicing.

title: chicken in pimiento sauce
directions: Roll chicken in seasoned flour, then roll chicken in melted butter.
Arrange in a single layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat vegetables in butter until tender.
Add cooked vegetables to the rest of the ingredients in order given, except the tomato sauce.
Mix ingredients; shape into loaf.
Place in baking dish; cover with tomato sauce.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Pat cream cheese on platter; layer with cocktail sauce, shrimp and green onions.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a 9 x 12-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle the chocolate chips and chopped pecans on cake.

title: rigsby bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water with sugar.
Add milk, Crisco, eggs and salt.
Place in greased bowl; let rise (1 hour) in warm place. Punch down; divide in half.
Put in pan; let rise 30 minutes. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecans to syrup mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Yield:
1 (9-inch) pie.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2-quart casserole with tight cover. Cover.
Bake in 300° oven for 3 hours.
Do not peek! Serve to 6 over steamed rice or noodles.

title: aunt otry lavinghouse's egg nog
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix egg yolks, sugar, milk, pudding mix and flavoring. Add egg whites and Cool Whip.
Mix well. Add nutmeg to taste.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Combine sugar and condensed milk and peanut butter in mixing bowl.
Stir until well blended, stir in chocolate morsels and chill until firm.
Shape into 3/4 in. balls and roll in chocolate sprinkles.
Chill until firm.

title: macaroni tuna salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix together all ingredients.

title: casserole
directions: Stir soup to make creamy consistency. Add rest of ingredients except the eggs. Mix, fold in eggs. Turn into buttered baking dish. Let stand in fridge 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Bake uncovered at 350 for 1 hour.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
For crust:
Combine flour and salt in medium bowl, cut in Crisco with pastry blender or 2 knives until flour is just blended in to form pea-size chunks.
Sprinkle with water, one tablespoon at a time.
Toss lightly with fork until dough will form a ball.
Press between hands to form 5 to 6-inch "pancake."
Flour rolling surface and rolling pin.
Roll dough into circle.
Trim one-inch larger than upside-down 9-inch pie plate. Loosen dough carefully.
Fold into quarters.
Unfold and press into pie plate, trim edge even with pie plate.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: all-in-one breakfast(diabetic)
directions: Spread cottage cheese over toast.
Add fruit.
Sprinkle with sweetener and apple pie spice.
Top with crushed cereal.
Broil or bake until warm.
Try different flavorings or spices to make delicious variations.

title: bloody eight
directions: In pitcher, stir together all ingredients, except lemon. Serve immediately over ice cubes in 10 ounce glasses.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Makes 2 cups or 2 servings.
Contains 50 calories per serving.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Mix ingredients in punch bowl or some creative container. Freeze overnight and serve. This is great for a refreshing drink on a hot summer night or for social gatherings. It's always a hit.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions; drain. Cook and stir chicken, mushrooms and celery in butter until celery is tender.
Add cream and heat.
Toss together hot fettuccine, cream mixture, cheese, salt and pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease.
Cut Velveeta cheese into small slices.
Then mix the hamburger, cheese, olives, mushrooms and salsa in crock-pot.
Let simmer on high until creamy.
Then turn on low.
Cut sour dough bread into slices just big enough to dip and eat.

title: cheesy beef rice bake
directions: In large saucepan, cook ground beef and garlic until meat is browned; drain off fat.
Remove from pan and set aside.
In same saucepan, cook uncooked rice in butter until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Stir in water, carrot, bouillon granules, parsley, dried onion, salt and basil.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in meat mixture.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, add beans, onion and olives; mix well with a spoon.
Add mayonnaise and olive juice.
Mix lightly the diced eggs.
Mix all through the mixture.
Let chill overnight.

title: pudding-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yields about 7 dozen.

title: m&m's surprises
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave or double boiler.
Add M&M's. Stir until they are covered.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: In buttered casserole dish, arrange chicken.
Place broccoli over chicken.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise and pepper and pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top, then sprinkle bread crumbs over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix corn oil and sugar together with spoon until sugar is dissolved.
Combine dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture alternately with eggs, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla, chopped apples, nuts and coconut.
Batter will be very thick. Pour into greased and floured tube pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: While rice is cooking, pound steak to 1/4 inch thickness. Cut into 1/4 inch wide strips.
Sprinkle meat with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
Using a large skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add garlic and broth.

title: italian bread
directions: Put flour in bowl and mix in yeast, salt and oil.
Add water and work/knead until velvety smooth.
Put in bowl; cover with cloth and let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down.
Knead 5 minutes. Shape into 2 loaves in greased pans.
Cover with cloth and let rise until doubled.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake for 25 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes more.
It will sound hollow when tapped.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over All-Bran cereal; mix and let stand to cool.
Mix and add the remaining ingredients.
Spray tins with Pam and fill 1/2 full.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Batter keeps 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix everything together. Pour in a 9 x 12 greased pan and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
tags: yellow self rising corn meal mix

title: potatoes and ham casserole
directions: Prepare peeled and sliced potatoes in bottom of casserole. Sprinkle some diced onion on, then some diced ham, then a few spoons of creamed corn.
Sprinkle some flour over all.
Keep layering until casserole is full.
Pour in milk.
Bake until potatoes are done in a 350° oven.

title: easy noodle casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion in a large skillet until onion is tender. Stir in noodles, tomato paste, tomatoes, 1 cup shredded cheese, seasonings and olives.
Turn into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, onion and pimento in a mixing bowl. Mix mayonnaise and chicken soup and stir into chicken-vegetable mixture.
Put into oblong casserole dish.
Top with egg slices, cheese, corn flakes and almonds.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
